Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.50,0:01:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad0\pos(190,260)\fad(1500,1500)}三千年的{\c&H000A0D5E&}渴望
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.42,0:01:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我叫Alithea\N{\rEng}My name is Alithea.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.16,0:01:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,我的故事是真实的\N{\rEng}My story is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.82,0:01:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,不过，如果我把它当做童话来讲\N{\rEng}You're more likely to believe me, however,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.21,0:01:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,你更有可能相信我\N{\rEng}if I tell it as a fairy tale.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.09,0:01:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,那么，很久很久以前\N{\rEng}So, once upon a time,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.74,0:01:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,当人类用金属翅膀猛地飞过天空时\N{\rEng}when humans hurtled across the sky on metal wings,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.40,0:01:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,当他们穿着有蹼的脚\N{\rEng}when they wore webbed feet
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.79,0:01:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,在海底行走时\N{\rEng}and walked on the bottom of the sea,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.40,0:01:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,当他们手里拿着\N{\rEng}when they held in their hands glass tiles
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.58,0:01:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,能在空气发出情歌的玻璃砖时…\N{\rEng}that could coax love songs from the air...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.84,0:01:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,有这么一个女人，她很快乐，也很孤独\N{\rEng}...there was a woman, adequately happy and alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.76,0:01:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,自我选择的孤独\N{\rEng}Alone by choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.68,0:01:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,快乐是因为她独立\N{\rEng}Happy because she was independent,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.59,0:02:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,以锻炼她的学术思想为生\N{\rEng}living off the exercise of her scholarly mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.77,0:02:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,她的事业是讲故事\N{\rEng}Her business was story.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.69,0:02:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,她是一位叙事学家\N{\rEng}She was a narratologist
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.43,0:02:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,试图找到人类所有故事中\N{\rEng}who sought to find the truths
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.21,0:02:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,共同的真理\N{\rEng}common to all the stories of humankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.43,0:02:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,为此\N{\rEng}To this end, once or twice a year,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.26,0:02:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,她每年都会去一到两次陌生的地方冒险\N{\rEng}she ventured to strange lands.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.87,0:02:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,去中国的南海\N{\rEng}To China, the South Seas,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.62,0:02:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,去黎凡特的永恒城市…\N{\rEng}and the timeless cities of the Levant...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.84,0:02:33.41,Default,,0,0,0,,在那里，她的同类聚集在一起，讲述故事\N{\rEng}where her kind gathered to tell stories about stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.85,0:02:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,这边\N{\rEng}This way.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.15,0:02:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,-对不起  -女士，这边\N{\rEng}-Excuse me. -This way, lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.20,0:02:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,你在做什么？ 你能放开手吗，拜托？\N{\rEng}What are you doing? Can you let go, please?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.85,0:02:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,伊斯坦布尔的奥秘\N{\rEng}The mysteries of Istanbul.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.46,0:02:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,-Alithea！\N{\rEng}-Alithea!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.73,0:02:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Alithea！\N{\rEng}Alithea!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.86,0:02:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,欢迎！\N{\rEng}Welcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.52,0:02:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,-终于来了！ 啊\N{\rEng}-Welcome at last! Aw. -Gunhan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.22,0:02:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,-我亲爱的朋友\N{\rEng}-My dear friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.35,0:03:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,-哦，多好啊！  -我很抱歉\N{\rEng}-Oh, how wonderful! -I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.83,0:03:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,-这是阿米娜  -阿米娜\N{\rEng}-This is Amina. -Amina.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.53,0:03:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,来自英国文化协会\N{\rEng}From the British Council.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.88,0:03:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,在机场的那个家伙对我的行李动手动脚\N{\rEng}That fellow at the airport manhandling my luggage,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.49,0:03:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,你看到他了吗？\N{\rEng}did you see him?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.71,0:03:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,哪个家伙？\N{\rEng}What fellow?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.32,0:03:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,你来的时候他就跑了\N{\rEng}He scuttled off when you arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.67,0:03:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,很矮小，穿着羊皮夹克，粉色领子\N{\rEng}Small, sheepskin jacket, pink collar.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.50,0:03:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,有趣\N{\rEng}Interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.63,0:03:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,他摸起来很热\N{\rEng}He was hot to touch.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.99,0:03:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,穆斯基\N{\rEng}Musky.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.81,0:03:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,也许他是一个精灵\N{\rEng}Perhaps he was a djinn.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.51,0:03:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,更有可能是一个非法出租车司机\N{\rEng}An illegal taxi driver, more likely.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.99,0:03:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,喷太多的古龙水了\N{\rEng}Wearing too much cologne.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.95,0:03:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,对了，教授\N{\rEng}So, Professor,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.82,0:03:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,你说你相信有精灵？\N{\rEng}you saying you believe in djinn?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.35,0:03:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,我相信，有的人需要相信他们\N{\rEng}I believe there are those who need to believe in them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.26,0:03:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,包括我吗？\N{\rEng}Including me?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.39,0:03:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,精灵，鬼魂\N{\rEng}Djinn, ghosts,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.61,0:03:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,外星人，任何有用的东西\N{\rEng}aliens, whatever helps.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.97,0:03:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,酒店为你安排了一个惊喜\N{\rEng}The hotel's arranged a lovely surprise for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.02,0:04:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,这是阿加莎·克里斯蒂的房间\N{\rEng}It's the Agatha Christie room.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.89,0:04:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,在这个房间里\N{\rEng}In this room,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.20,0:04:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,她写了《东方快车谋杀案》\N{\rEng}she wrote Murder on the Orient Express.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.86,0:04:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,那么，如果你没有\N{\rEng}So, how would you explain
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.60,0:04:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,测量和模拟气象数据的方法？\N{\rEng}the power of a thunderstorm
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.00,0:04:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,你怎么解释\N{\rEng}if you don't have the means
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.39,0:04:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,雷雨的力量？\N{\rEng}to measure and model meteorological data?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.61,0:04:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你不知道\N{\rEng}How can you explain the seasons?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.79,0:04:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,地球在轴上倾斜着\N{\rEng}Autumn through winter to spring and summer,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.57,0:04:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,围绕太阳运行\N{\rEng}if you don't know that the Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.75,0:04:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,你怎么能解释四季呢？\N{\rEng}orbits the Sun while tilted on an axis?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.58,0:04:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,一切都是神秘的\N{\rEng}Everything was mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.67,0:04:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,季节、海啸、微生物疾病…\N{\rEng}The seasons, tsunamis, microbial disease...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.76,0:04:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,除了求助于故事，我们还能做什么？\N{\rEng}What else could we do but resort to stories?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.85,0:04:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,正如Binnie博士鼓励我们理解的那样\N{\rEng}As Dr. Binnie has encouraged us to understand,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.90,0:04:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,故事是使我们令人困惑的存在\N{\rEng}stories were once the only way
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.99,0:04:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,变得连贯的唯一途径\N{\rEng}to make our bewildering existence coherent.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.56,0:05:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,这是完全正确的\N{\rEng}That's exactly right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.34,0:05:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,我们为所有奇迹和灾难\N{\rEng}We gave name to the unknown forces
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.04,0:05:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,背后的未知力量命名\N{\rEng}behind all wonder and catastrophe,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.08,0:05:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,通过相互讲述…\N{\rEng}by telling each other...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.87,0:05:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,通过相互讲述彼此的故事\N{\rEng}By telling each other stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.92,0:05:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,-让我给大家展示一下\N{\rEng}-let me show you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.70,0:05:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,我们讲述了具体的、强大的、可亲近的神的故事\N{\rEng}We told tales of specific, powerful, relatable gods
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.45,0:05:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,这些神永远存在于所有的文化中，在所有的神话中\N{\rEng}ever present in all cultures, in all mythologies,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.84,0:05:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,从希腊人，到罗马人，到北欧人\N{\rEng}from the Greeks, to the Romans, to the Norse,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.89,0:05:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,等等  诸如此类\N{\rEng}and so on, and so on.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.76,0:05:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,熟悉的宙斯、波塞冬、雅典娜、\N{\rEng}The familiar descendant of Zeus, Poseidon, Athena,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.11,0:05:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,托尔等人的后裔\N{\rEng}Thor, the whole gang,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.68,0:05:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,即使在今天也能找到表达方式\N{\rEng}find expression even today.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.81,0:05:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,这些就是他们遗留的痕迹\N{\rEng}These are their vestiges.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.43,0:05:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,问题是，他们的目的是什么？\N{\rEng}The question remains, what is their purpose?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.39,0:05:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,我们现在对他们有什么要求？\N{\rEng}What do we require of them now?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.53,0:06:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,这里有神话，也有科学\N{\rEng}There is mythos, and there is science.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.66,0:06:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,哦  对不起\N{\rEng}Oh. Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.14,0:06:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,神话是我们过去知道的\N{\rEng}Mythology is what we knew back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.63,0:06:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,科学是我们目前所知道的\N{\rEng}Science is what we know so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.42,0:06:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,迟早\N{\rEng}Sooner or later,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.77,0:06:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,我们的创造故事会被\N{\rEng}our creation stories are replaced
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.60,0:06:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,科学的叙述所取代\N{\rEng}by the narratives of science.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.51,0:06:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,勤勉的科学\N{\rEng}Painstaking science.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.91,0:06:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,而所有的神和怪兽\N{\rEng}And all gods and monsters
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.91,0:06:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,都会比它们本来的含义活得更久\N{\rEng}outlive their original purpose
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.09,0:06:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,最后沦为隐喻\N{\rEng}and are reduced to metaphor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.57,0:06:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,胡说八道！\N{\rEng}Rubbish!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.57,0:06:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Alithea！\N{\rEng}Alithea!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.19,0:06:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Alithea\N{\rEng}Alithea.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.54,0:06:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,发生了什么事？\N{\rEng}What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.71,0:06:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道，她只是摔倒了\N{\rEng}I don't know. She just fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.15,0:06:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,-她只是摔倒了\N{\rEng}-She just fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.98,0:07:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,你还好吗？\N{\rEng}Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.08,0:07:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,你不应该去看医生吗？\N{\rEng}Shouldn't you see a doctor?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.52,0:07:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么？当我感觉这么好的时候去看医生？\N{\rEng}Why? When I feel so well?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.04,0:07:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,请原谅我，Alithea  你确定吗？\N{\rEng}Forgive me, Alithea. Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.48,0:07:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,除了有点痛\N{\rEng}Apart from the usual aches and pains,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.74,0:07:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,没有什么不舒服的地方\N{\rEng}there is nothing untoward.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.44,0:07:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,没有理由大惊小怪的\N{\rEng}There's no reason to make a fuss.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.14,0:07:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,那么，刚刚发生了什么？\N{\rEng}So, what happened back there?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.10,0:07:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,最近，我的想象力越来越丰富了\N{\rEng}Lately, my imagination's been getting the better of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.71,0:07:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,它突然涌向我\N{\rEng}Ambushing me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.72,0:07:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,我想这是一个警告\N{\rEng}I think it's a warning.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.89,0:07:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,关于什么？\N{\rEng}About what?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.59,0:07:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,不要自满\N{\rEng}Not to be complacent.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.59,0:07:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,要保持警惕\N{\rEng}To keep on my toes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.94,0:07:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,它不时地表现得很粗鲁\N{\rEng}It manifests rudely from time to time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.60,0:07:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我试着不去反抗它\N{\rEng}I try not to fight it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.16,0:07:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,它控制了一会儿，然后就消退了\N{\rEng}It takes charge for a moment, and then it steps back.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.99,0:07:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,什么消退？\N{\rEng}What steps back?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.56,0:08:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,哦，Gunhan这都是胡思乱想  你不要在意\N{\rEng}Oh, Gunhan, it's irrational. Pay it no mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.09,0:08:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,你的行为像个孩子  你知道吗？\N{\rEng}You are behaving like a child. Do you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.52,0:08:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道，我其实就是个孩子\N{\rEng}You know, I am actually a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.27,0:08:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,如果有命运，我们能逃脱它吗？\N{\rEng}If there is fate, can we escape it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.84,0:08:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,谁能说？\N{\rEng}Who can say?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.84,0:08:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,但我告诉你\N{\rEng}But I tell you this,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.02,0:08:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,在伊斯坦布尔的大巴扎里\N{\rEng}in the Grand Bazaar of Istanbul,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.24,0:08:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,有62条街道和4000家商店\N{\rEng}there are 62 streets and 4,000 shops.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.15,0:08:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,而在其中一个商店里，有三个房间\N{\rEng}And in one of those shops, there are three rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.55,0:08:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,在其中最小的一个房间里\N{\rEng}In the smallest of those rooms,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.20,0:08:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,有一堆没有分类的东西\N{\rEng}there was a pile of things unsorted,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.81,0:08:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,有旧的也有新的\N{\rEng}old and new.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.56,0:08:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,从那堆东西的最底下\N{\rEng}From the bottom of that pile,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.52,0:08:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,我选择了一个纪念品\N{\rEng}I chose a memento.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.00,0:08:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道这是什么吗？\N{\rEng}Do you know what this is?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.83,0:08:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,我不确定，但它可能是Cesm-i Bulbul\N{\rEng}I'm not sure, but it could be Cesm-i Bulbul,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.70,0:08:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,夜莺之眼"\N{\rEng}a "Nightingale's Eye."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.23,0:08:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,1845年左右，在Incirkoy有些玻璃制造商\N{\rEng}Around 1845, there were these glassmakers in Incirkoy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.58,0:09:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,他们以这种螺旋形的蓝白色图案而闻名\N{\rEng}They were famous for this spiral blue-white pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.19,0:09:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,哦，拜托  这是我送的礼物\N{\rEng}Oh, please. It's a gift from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.23,0:09:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,选一些不那么悲凉的东西吧\N{\rEng}Choose something less forlorn.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.54,0:09:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,还有，呃，如果这是Cesm-i Bulbul\N{\rEng}And, uh, if this is Cesm-i Bulbul,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.33,0:09:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,呃，有什么办法可以验证它吗？\N{\rEng}uh, is there a way of authenticating it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.85,0:09:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,嗯，他们说，如果是真的\N{\rEng}Well, they say that if it is genuine,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.59,0:09:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,有时你可以看到血迹\N{\rEng}sometimes you can see specks of blood
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.60,0:09:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,是来自吹玻璃的人肺里的\N{\rEng}from the lungs of the glassblowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.03,0:09:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,但这更可能是近期的仿品\N{\rEng}But this is more likely a recent imitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.25,0:09:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,它已经被火烧坏了  选点别的吧\N{\rEng}It's been damaged by fire. Pick something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.78,0:09:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,不用了，谢谢你，Gunhan\N{\rEng}No, thank you, Gunhan.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.17,0:09:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,我喜欢\N{\rEng}I like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.70,0:09:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,不管它是什么，我相信它一定有一个有趣的故事\N{\rEng}Whatever it is, I'm sure it has an interesting story.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.07,0:10:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,哪位？\N{\rEng}Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.16,0:10:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,早上好， Binnie博士\N{\rEng}Good morning, Dr. Binnie.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.38,0:10:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,-早上好  -这是客房服务\N{\rEng}-Good morning. -This is room service.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.90,0:10:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,-是的  -你喜欢鸡蛋吗？\N{\rEng}-Yes. -How do you like your eggs?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.12,0:10:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,呃，溏心蛋，谢谢\N{\rEng}Er, runny, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.69,0:10:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,-和土司一起吃？  -是的，但不能有面包皮\N{\rEng}-And with toast? -Yes, but no crusts.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.08,0:10:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,-两个蛋？  -只要一个\N{\rEng}-Two eggs? -Just one.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.26,0:10:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,-好的，谢谢  -谢谢\N{\rEng}-Okay, thank you. -Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.26,0:11:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我将闭上眼睛，数到三\N{\rEng}I'm going to close my eyes and count to three,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.96,0:11:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你能离开\N{\rEng}after which I would be grateful
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.31,0:11:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,我将非常感激\N{\rEng}if you would be gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.01,0:11:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,1！\N{\rEng}One,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.75,0:11:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,2！\N{\rEng}two,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.84,0:11:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,3！\N{\rEng}three.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.85,0:12:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,4！\N{\rEng}Four,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.46,0:12:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,5！\N{\rEng}five,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.85,0:12:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,6！\N{\rEng}six,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.33,0:12:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,7，8\N{\rEng}seven, eight,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.38,0:12:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,9，10\N{\rEng}nine, ten.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.18,0:12:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,我想你不会说英语吧？\N{\rEng}I don't suppose you speak English?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.06,0:12:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,德语？\N{\rEng}Deutsch?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.19,0:12:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,西班牙语？\N{\rEng}Espanol?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.41,0:12:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,埃利尼卡？\N{\rEng}Ellinika?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.50,0:12:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5\c&H0000C2CD&}你说荷马的希腊语?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.95,0:12:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5\c&H0000C2CD&}我在大学学过一些
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.50,0:12:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5\c&H0000C2CD&}请别怕我
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.50,0:13:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5\c&H0000C2CD&}也不要随便对待我
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.50,0:13:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5\c&H0000C2CD&}我很感激你放我出来
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.50,0:13:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5\c&H0000C2CD&}为此，我必须满足你三个愿望
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.50,0:13:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5\c&H0000C2CD&}这个规则不能破
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.50,0:13:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5\c&H0000C2CD&}只能是三
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.50,0:13:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5\c&H0000C2CD&}这个充满力量的数字
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.55,0:13:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5\c&H0000C2CD&}你不能无止尽的许愿
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.00,0:13:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5\c&H0000C2CD&}明白
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.50,0:13:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5\c&H0000C2CD&}我很了解这规则
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.50,0:13:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5\c&H0000C2CD&}你也不能许愿得到永生
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.50,0:13:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5\c&H0000C2CD&}你的本性是凡人
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.50,0:13:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5\c&H0000C2CD&}我的本性是不朽
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.50,0:13:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5\c&H0000C2CD&}我也不能赦免罪恶或结束所有的痛苦
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.50,0:13:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5\c&H0000C2CD&}我只是精灵
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.50,0:13:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5\c&H0000C2CD&}这很合理
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.50,0:13:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5\c&H0000C2CD&}就是以上这些限制了
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.20,0:14:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5\c&H0000C2CD&}这个小东西是谁？
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.50,0:14:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5\c&H0000C2CD&}他是个  巫师
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.50,0:14:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5\c&H0000C2CD&}引导我们穿越时空
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.93,0:14:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,爱因斯坦\N{\rEng}Einstein.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.98,0:14:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,爱因斯坦\N{\rEng}Einstein.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.50,0:14:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5\c&H0000C2CD&}你是把他关在这箱子里的女巫吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.00,0:14:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5\c&H0000C2CD&}不
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.50,0:14:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5\c&H0000C2CD&}这是科学
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.49,0:14:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,电视\N{\rEng}Television.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.50,0:14:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5\c&H0000C2CD&}能发出光和声波
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.67,0:14:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,发射器\N{\rEng}Transmitters.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.50,0:14:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5\c&H0000C2CD&}我不太了解它的工作原理
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.50,0:14:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5\c&H0000C2CD&}我是个文学家
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.50,0:14:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5\c&H0000C2CD&}我们所知不多
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.40,0:14:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,我是一个能力不强的精灵\N{\rEng}I am a djinn of modest power,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.31,0:14:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,但我开始理解这些传输信号\N{\rEng}but I begin to understand these transmissions.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.93,0:14:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,哦！\N{\rEng}Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.28,0:14:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,你已经学会说我的语言了\N{\rEng}You've learned to speak my language.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.63,0:14:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,这个英语很直截了当\N{\rEng}This English is straightforward.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.63,0:14:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,我发现，它的规则学得很快\N{\rEng}Its rules quickly learn, I find.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.20,0:15:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,我的意思是说\N{\rEng}Nein, nein, nein.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.60,0:15:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,你想把这个小艾伯特留给自己吗？\N{\rEng}Would you like this little Albert for yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.99,0:15:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,不，不，不\N{\rEng}No, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.34,0:15:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,这对他可不是好事  把他放回去\N{\rEng}That can't be good for him. Put him back.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.90,0:15:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,-我可以放大他  -怎么做？\N{\rEng}-I could expand him. -How?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.17,0:15:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,我们可以和他说话\N{\rEng}We could speak with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.38,0:15:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,-这怎么可能呢？  -不，把他放回去\N{\rEng}-How is this possible? -No, put him back.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.91,0:15:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,-这是你的愿望吗？  -这是不可能的\N{\rEng}-Is that your wish? -This is not possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.65,0:15:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,不，这是你的义务\N{\rEng}No. It's your obligation.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.92,0:15:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,那么，你会希望得到什么？\N{\rEng}So, what will you wish for?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.92,0:15:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,你心中的愿望是什么？\N{\rEng}What is your heart's desire?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.19,0:15:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,现在，让我们，呃，不要急于求成\N{\rEng}Now, let's, uh, not get ahead of ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.02,0:15:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,我需要慢慢来\N{\rEng}I need to take this slow.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.02,0:15:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,我拥有世界上所有的时间\N{\rEng}I have all the time in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.37,0:15:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,告诉我你的情况\N{\rEng}Tell me about yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.46,0:15:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,我的名字是阿利特哈-宾尼\N{\rEng}My name is Alithea Binnie.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.47,0:15:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,我在土耳其参加一个会议\N{\rEng}I am in Turkey for a conference.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.99,0:15:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,我在一天内就会回我的国家\N{\rEng}And I return to my homeland in a day's time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.43,0:15:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,还有呢？\N{\rEng}Also?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.34,0:16:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,另外，我有件事要坦白\N{\rEng}Also, I have a confession to make.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.26,0:16:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,我从来没有告诉过别人的事情\N{\rEng}Something I've never told anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.31,0:16:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,很好\N{\rEng}Excellent.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.96,0:16:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我小的时候，有一个男孩\N{\rEng}When I was young, there was a boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.75,0:16:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,你的初恋情人？\N{\rEng}Your first lover?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.27,0:16:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,不，不，不  他不是血肉之躯\N{\rEng}No, no, no. He was not of flesh and blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.19,0:16:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,一个精灵？\N{\rEng}A djinn?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.45,0:16:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,不是\N{\rEng}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.58,0:16:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,那时候，我发现自己在一所女子学校\N{\rEng}At that time, I found myself in a school for girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.45,0:16:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,成群结队的女孩\N{\rEng}Gaggles of girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.37,0:16:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我是… 嗯，我天生是个孤独的生物\N{\rEng}I was... Well, I am a solitary creature by nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.20,0:16:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,还有这个男孩，恩佐\N{\rEng}And this boy, Enzo,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.25,0:16:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,他来到我身边，从空虚中走来\N{\rEng}he came to me, out of an emptiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.42,0:16:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,出于一种想象的需要\N{\rEng}Out of a need to imagine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.38,0:16:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,他用一种只有我们两个人说的语言\N{\rEng}He told me stories in a language
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.30,0:16:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,给我讲故事\N{\rEng}that only we two spoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.09,0:16:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,而且他总是在我头疼的时候消失\N{\rEng}And he always disappeared when I had a headache,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.26,0:16:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,但当我因为哮喘而不能动的时候\N{\rEng}but he was never far away
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.52,0:16:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,他从未远离过我\N{\rEng}when I couldn't move for asthma.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.00,0:16:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,他就像这个小艾伯特\N{\rEng}He was like this little Albert
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.70,0:16:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,你不愿意让我给你？\N{\rEng}you would not let me give you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.31,0:16:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,显灵？\N{\rEng}An emanation?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.23,0:16:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,只是一个不存在的显灵\N{\rEng}Only an emanation of an absence.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.15,0:17:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,我担心他会离开，所以我把他写下来\N{\rEng}I feared he would leave, and so I wrote him down.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.50,0:17:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,我把这本日记写得满满的，充满了故事\N{\rEng}And I filled this journal, bulging with facts.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.50,0:17:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,但我越是试图插入现实主义\N{\rEng}But the more realism I tried to insert,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.68,0:17:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,我就越是开始怀疑\N{\rEng}the more I began to doubt,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.69,0:17:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,而且，呃，这一切都开始感觉很愚蠢\N{\rEng}and, uh, it all began to feel silly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.13,0:17:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得很傻\N{\rEng}I felt silly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.52,0:17:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,所以，过了一段时间\N{\rEng}So, after a time,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.17,0:17:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,我在学校的炉子里把它全烧了\N{\rEng}I burned it all in the school furnace.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.70,0:17:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,在那之后，他就完全消失了\N{\rEng}And after that, he disappeared altogether.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.79,0:17:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,然而，我还在这里\N{\rEng}And yet, I am here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.62,0:17:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,违反情理，没错\N{\rEng}Contrary to reason, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.76,0:17:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我在这里，我们有事要做\N{\rEng}I am here, and we have work to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.33,0:17:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,请稍后再来好吗？\N{\rEng}Can you come back later, please?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.72,0:17:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,这是客房服务，宾尼博士\N{\rEng}It's room service, Dr. Binnie.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.68,0:17:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,我把你的早餐送来了\N{\rEng}I have your breakfast.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.73,0:18:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,稍等片刻！\N{\rEng}Just a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.42,0:18:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,必须关门\N{\rEng}Must close door.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.31,0:18:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,早上好\N{\rEng}Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.44,0:18:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,你想在哪里吃？宾尼博士\N{\rEng}Where would you like it, Dr. Binnie?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.66,0:18:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢你  哦，我可以拿着它\N{\rEng}Thank you. Oh, I can take it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.92,0:18:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,-请允许我  -不，不，我可以处理\N{\rEng}-Please, allow me. -No. No, I can manage it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.23,0:18:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,很好，宾尼博士  我希望你休息好了\N{\rEng}Jolly good, Dr. Binnie. I hope you are well rested.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.84,0:18:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,哦，这看起来很好吃  是的，我是\N{\rEng}Oh, that looks delicious. Yes, I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.58,0:18:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,今天天气不错，你打算做什么？\N{\rEng}What do you plan to do on this fine day?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.41,0:18:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,呃，我不确定  我在即兴创作\N{\rEng}Uh, I'm not sure. I'm improvising.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.15,0:18:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,嗯，我想给你介绍一个美丽的艺术馆…\N{\rEng}Well, I'd like to show you a beautiful art gallery...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.63,0:18:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,你真是太客气了  谢谢你\N{\rEng}That's so kind. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.85,0:18:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,…今天下午，当你有机会的时候\N{\rEng}...this afternoon, when you get a chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.02,0:18:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,-也许下次吧  -这会很不错的\N{\rEng}-Maybe another time. -It will be great.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.37,0:18:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢你  祝你有个美好的一天\N{\rEng}Thank you. Have a beautiful day.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.42,0:18:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,好的  请享用\N{\rEng}Okay. Jolly good. Enjoy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.59,0:18:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢你！\N{\rEng}Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.20,0:19:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,更合适的尺寸，我明白了\N{\rEng}A more convenient size, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.81,0:19:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,我尽我所能去适应\N{\rEng}I do what I can to fit in.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.21,0:19:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,请吧\N{\rEng}Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.16,0:19:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,我不需要点早餐\N{\rEng}I needn't have ordered breakfast.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.34,0:19:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,这是nan-e nokhodchi  鹰嘴豆,丁香,开心果\N{\rEng}It's nan-e nokhodchi. Chickpeas, cloves, pistachio.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.82,0:19:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,它会在你的嘴里融化\N{\rEng}It will melt in your mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.74,0:19:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,我可以问你一件事吗？\N{\rEng}May I ask you something?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.74,0:19:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,什么都可以\N{\rEng}Anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.31,0:19:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,你怎么会进到我的瓶子里的？\N{\rEng}How come you found your way into my bottle?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.40,0:19:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,啊，这是个很好的故事\N{\rEng}Ah, it's quite a story.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.71,0:19:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,那是我第三次被监禁\N{\rEng}That was my third incarceration.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.80,0:19:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,你已经被困在瓶子里三次了？\N{\rEng}You've been trapped in a bottle three times?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.89,0:20:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我也许是个精灵\N{\rEng}I may be a djinn, but I'm also a fool
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.24,0:20:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,但我也是个喜欢和女人的谈话的傻子\N{\rEng}with too great a fondness for the conversation of women.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.85,0:20:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我以后要更加小心\N{\rEng}I need to be more careful in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.24,0:20:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,你当初是怎么被抓住的？\N{\rEng}How were you caught in the first place?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.51,0:20:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,靠欲望\N{\rEng}By desire.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.20,0:20:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,还想知道什么呢？\N{\rEng}How else?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.73,0:20:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,她是谁？\N{\rEng}Who was she?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.34,0:20:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Sheba\N{\rEng}Sheba.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.82,0:20:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,示巴女王？\N{\rEng}The Queen of Sheba?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.21,0:20:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,她是我的亲戚\N{\rEng}She was my kin.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.74,0:20:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,她是一个精灵？\N{\rEng}She was a djinn?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.87,0:20:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,她的母亲是个精灵\N{\rEng}Her mother was a djinn.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.39,0:20:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,这有可能吗？\N{\rEng}Is that possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.48,0:20:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,有一些法律允许\N{\rEng}There are laws that allow
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.70,0:20:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,精灵和凡人结合\N{\rEng}the union of djinn and mortals,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.22,0:20:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,但他们不能生出永生的子孙\N{\rEng}but they cannot produce an immortal scion
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.96,0:20:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,就像驴和马\N{\rEng}the way a donkey and a horse
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.27,0:20:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,只能生出无法生育的骡子一样\N{\rEng}can only produce a seedless mule.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.88,0:20:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,那么，她是什么样子的呢？\N{\rEng}So, what did she look like?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.01,0:20:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,除了腿上浓密的绒毛外\N{\rEng}Other than a thick glade of black hair on her legs,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.23,0:20:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,她看起来和其他人类一样\N{\rEng}she looked like any other human being,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.63,0:20:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,除了，当然，她是示巴\N{\rEng}except, of course, she was Sheba.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.93,0:20:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,大家都说她很漂亮\N{\rEng}By all accounts, she was very beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.54,0:20:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,她不是漂亮  她就是美本尊\N{\rEng}She was not beautiful. She was beauty itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.03,0:20:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,我在各方面都是自由的\N{\rEng}I was in every way free.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.86,0:20:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,我可以在她的卧室里进进出出\N{\rEng}I would come in and out of her sleeping chamber.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.99,0:21:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Sheba…\N{\rEng}Sheba...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.00,0:21:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我和她的女奴一样清楚\N{\rEng}I knew as well as any of her female slaves
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.91,0:21:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,那种触摸会让她幸福得发抖\N{\rEng}the touches that made her shiver with bliss.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.05,0:21:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,我从来没有这么想要一个人\N{\rEng}Never have I wanted a creature so.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.40,0:21:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,她想要你作为回报吗？\N{\rEng}And she desired you in return?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.88,0:21:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,我是她的玩具  她的知己\N{\rEng}I was her plaything. Her confidante.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.28,0:21:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,要不是所罗门，我可能会变得更厉害\N{\rEng}I might have become more, but for Solomon.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.54,0:21:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,所罗门王？\N{\rEng}King Solomon?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.76,0:21:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,受神眷顾之人\N{\rEng}Blessed be his memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.76,0:21:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,他穿越沙漠来追求她\N{\rEng}He came from across the deserts to woo her.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.02,0:21:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,她没有去找他吗？\N{\rEng}Didn't she go to him?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.33,0:21:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,不  从来没有\N{\rEng}No. Never.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.68,0:21:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,但圣经上都写着呢\N{\rEng}But it's in all the holy books.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.50,0:21:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,所有的故事和画\N{\rEng}All the stories and the paintings.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.98,0:21:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,亨德尔为此创作了音乐\N{\rEng}And Handel wrote music about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.77,0:21:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,夫人，我当时在场\N{\rEng}Madam, I was there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.38,0:21:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,所罗门来到她身边-\N{\rEng}Solomon came to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.00,0:21:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5}你是自由的女王，就像一只强大的鸟，用公正的眼睛观察一切，
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.50,0:21:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5}你为什么要把自己绑在人的床上？
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.50,0:21:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5}亲爱的精灵，没有人能像你这样欺骗我
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.45,0:22:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,他从音乐开始\N{\rEng}he began with music.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.07,0:23:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,我尽我所能劝阻她\N{\rEng}I did all that I could to dissuade her.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.46,0:23:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,但当她\N{\rEng}But when she used
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.59,0:23:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,用贾巴沙蜜蜂的香蜡\N{\rEng}the scented wax of the Jabassa Bee
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.46,0:23:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,去掉腿上的毛时\N{\rEng}to remove the hair from her legs,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.03,0:23:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道我输了\N{\rEng}I knew that I was lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.73,0:23:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,但我像个傻瓜一样，继续告诉她\N{\rEng}But I, like a fool, went on telling her
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.08,0:23:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,她的身体富足而可爱\N{\rEng}that her body was rich and lovely,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.08,0:23:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,但她的思想更富足，更可爱\N{\rEng}but her mind was richer and lovelier,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.74,0:24:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,也更能持久\N{\rEng}and more durable.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.52,0:24:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,她同意我所说的一切\N{\rEng}And she agreed with all that I said,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.61,0:24:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,并流下了一滴热泪\N{\rEng}and dropped a hot tear.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.61,0:24:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,她开始给他布置似乎是不可能的任务\N{\rEng}She began to set him tasks, which seemed impossible,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.62,0:24:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,要他在千百个房间的宫殿里\N{\rEng}to find a particular thread of red silk
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.75,0:24:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,找到一条特别的红丝线\N{\rEng}in the palace of a thousand rooms,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.75,0:24:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,要他猜测她精灵母亲的秘密名字\N{\rEng}to guess the secret name of her mother djinn,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.62,0:24:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,要他告诉她女人最渴望的东西\N{\rEng}to tell her what women most desire.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.93,0:24:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,这看起来确实不可能\N{\rEng}That does seem impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.80,0:24:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,对他来说不是\N{\rEng}Not for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.06,0:24:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,他能与地上的野兽交谈\N{\rEng}He could speak to the beasts of the earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.59,0:24:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,也能与由精妙之火化作的精灵交谈\N{\rEng}and to the djinn made of subtle fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.02,0:24:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,他找到了蚂蚁来寻找丝线\N{\rEng}He found ants to discover the thread of silk,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.11,0:24:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,找到了一只妖精来低语母亲的名字\N{\rEng}and an ifrit to whisper the mother's name.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.51,0:24:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,然后他看着她的眼睛\N{\rEng}Then he looked into her eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.04,0:24:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,告诉她女人最渴望什么\N{\rEng}and told her what women most desire.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.22,0:24:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,她感到很惊讶\N{\rEng}She was astonished,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.18,0:24:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,并告诉他，他是对的\N{\rEng}and told him he was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.53,0:24:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,于是她答应了他最想得到的东西\N{\rEng}And so she granted him what he most desired,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.05,0:24:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,那就是与她结婚并被带到她的床上\N{\rEng}which was to wed her and be taken to her bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.03,0:25:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,他是一个伟大的魔术师…\N{\rEng}He was a great magician...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.82,0:25:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,用一句话\N{\rEng}-...and imprisoned me
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.30,0:25:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,就把我禁锢在一个铜瓶里\N{\rEng}with a word of power into a brass bottle.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.68,0:25:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,她没有为我求情\N{\rEng}She made no plea for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.81,0:25:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我对她来说什么都不是\N{\rEng}I was nothing to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.20,0:25:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,一息之间\N{\rEng}A breath in a bottle.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.87,0:26:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,就这样，我被扔进了红海\N{\rEng}And so, I was cast into the Red Sea
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.66,0:26:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,苦苦煎熬了2500年\N{\rEng}and languished for 2,500 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.62,0:26:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,除了睡觉\N{\rEng}Apart from sleep,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.23,0:26:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,在瓶子里呆了2500年还能做什么？\N{\rEng}what does one do in a bottle for 2,500 years?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.72,0:26:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,精灵不睡觉\N{\rEng}Djinn don't sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.90,0:26:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,那么，你是怎么渡过的呢？\N{\rEng}So, how do you manage then?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.90,0:26:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,在最初的100年里，我对我的命运感到愤怒\N{\rEng}Well, for the first 100 years, I rage against my fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.65,0:26:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,我向Boschkolo祈祷，希望得到释放\N{\rEng}I pray to Boschkolo for my release,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.39,0:26:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,如果这不起作用\N{\rEng}and when that does not work,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.82,0:26:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我就向我知道的任何神祈祷\N{\rEng}I pray to any god I know,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.30,0:26:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,然后再向我可能不知道的任何神祈祷\N{\rEng}and then to any god I may not know.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.26,0:26:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,当我仍然找不到答案时\N{\rEng}And when, still, I find no answers,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.05,0:27:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,我就在清醒的梦中\N{\rEng}I spend my time in waking dreams
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.14,0:27:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,重温我生命中的所有故事\N{\rEng}revisiting all the stories of my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.92,0:27:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,当我精疲力尽了很多很多次\N{\rEng}And when I have exhausted this many, many times,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.88,0:27:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,我又回到了我的祈祷和愤怒中\N{\rEng}I return to my prayer and my rage.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.93,0:27:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,然而，最后\N{\rEng}And then, finally,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.24,0:27:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,我对自己开了个玩笑\N{\rEng}I play a trick on myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.81,0:27:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,我祈祷留在瓶子里\N{\rEng}I pray to remain in the bottle.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.28,0:27:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,我恳求Boschkolo让我永远留在瓶子里\N{\rEng}I beseech Boschkolo to keep me always in the bottle.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.11,0:27:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,那这样做有用吗？\N{\rEng}And does that work?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.68,0:27:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,渴望一无所有？\N{\rEng}To yearn for nothing?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.16,0:27:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,假装什么都不想要\N{\rEng}To pretend to want nothing more
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.03,0:27:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,只想装在瓶子里？\N{\rEng}than to be contained in a bottle?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.77,0:27:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,不\N{\rEng}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.25,0:27:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,对于精灵来说，这是我们离死亡最近的一次\N{\rEng}For a djinn, it is the closest we ever come to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.87,0:27:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道她那道问题的答案吗？\N{\rEng}Do you know the answer to her question?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.65,0:27:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,女人最想要的是什么？\N{\rEng}What women most desire?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.83,0:27:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.96,0:27:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,你不知道吗？\N{\rEng}Do you not know?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.70,0:27:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你不知道，我也不能告诉你\N{\rEng}If you do not know, I cannot tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.22,0:27:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,当然，我们想要的东西不都是一样的\N{\rEng}Well, surely, we don't all want the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.40,0:27:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,夫人，你的渴望我一点也不清楚\N{\rEng}Madam, your yearnings are not at all clear to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.01,0:27:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,我…我目前一切所需都已拥有\N{\rEng}I... I'm at a point in my life where I have all I need.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.32,0:27:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,我敢说我很满足，而且很感激\N{\rEng}I daresay I'm content, and gratefully so.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.89,0:27:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,告诉我\N{\rEng}Tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.02,0:27:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,你是妻子吗？一个寡妇吗？\N{\rEng}Are you a wife? A widow?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.41,0:28:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,-恩…—也许是母亲？\N{\rEng}-Um... -A mother, perhaps?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.68,0:28:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我没有孩子，没有兄弟姐妹，没有父母\N{\rEng}I have no children, no siblings, no parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.98,0:28:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,我曾经有过一个丈夫\N{\rEng}I did once have a husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.29,0:28:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah\N{\rEng}Ah.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.55,0:28:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,这个丈夫的肤色是什么？\N{\rEng}And what was the complexion of this husband?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.21,0:28:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,他的肤色吗？\N{\rEng}His complexion?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.69,0:28:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,一开始，它是发光的\N{\rEng}In the beginning, it was glowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.86,0:28:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,最后呢？\N{\rEng}And in the ending?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.69,0:28:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,这算不上什么故事\N{\rEng}It's not much of a story.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.21,0:28:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,但这是一个故事  这是你的故事\N{\rEng}But it is a story. It is your story,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.13,0:28:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,了解那些控制你的人\N{\rEng}and it is always wise
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.78,0:28:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,是明智的\N{\rEng}to understand those who have a hold on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.74,0:28:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,请继续\N{\rEng}Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.01,0:28:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧，好吧，嗯\N{\rEng}Well, okay, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.71,0:28:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,我们从年轻时就认识对方\N{\rEng}We'd known each other since our youth.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.19,0:28:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,我们，嗯，结婚很早\N{\rEng}We, uh, married early.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.06,0:28:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,一开始，我们在对方的思想\N{\rEng}In the beginning, we took pleasure
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.02,0:28:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,和身体上获得快乐\N{\rEng}in each other's minds and bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.85,0:28:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,嗯…\N{\rEng}Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.19,0:28:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,我们舒舒服服地度过了那几年\N{\rEng}We passed the years comfortably,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.02,0:28:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,然后，一切都\N{\rEng}and then as it happens,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.16,0:28:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,消失了\N{\rEng}it all evaporated,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.20,0:28:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,然后，呃…我们变得\N{\rEng}and, uh... and we became
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.38,0:28:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,越来越少交流\N{\rEng}less.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.42,0:28:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,他在哪里？\N{\rEng}And where is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.12,0:29:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,他和艾米琳·波特在哈克尼\N{\rEng}He's in Hackney, with Emmeline Porter.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.08,0:29:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,嗯\N{\rEng}Mmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.44,0:29:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,他告诉我…\N{\rEng}He told me I...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.39,0:29:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,我无法读懂感情\N{\rEng}I was incapable of reading feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.01,0:29:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,我无法读懂他的感情\N{\rEng}I was incapable of reading his feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.36,0:29:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,得做个决定了\N{\rEng}...gonna have a resolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.28,0:29:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,这太棒了！\N{\rEng}This is exciting!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.45,0:29:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,-这太棒了！-不，不\N{\rEng}-It is exciting! -No, it's not.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.02,0:29:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,让我猜猜看  没有人死在里面\N{\rEng}Let me guess. No one dies in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.45,0:29:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,不\N{\rEng}No!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.19,0:29:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,我的大脑思维方式是…是…\N{\rEng}The way my brain is wired is... is the...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.02,0:29:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,是我的力量和\N{\rEng}the source both of my power
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.03,0:29:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,呃，和我的孤独的来源\N{\rEng}and, uh, and my solitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.77,0:29:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,我怀疑这就是我喜欢故事的原因\N{\rEng}I suspect that's why I like stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.86,0:29:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,我通过故事找到感觉\N{\rEng}I find feelings through stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.08,0:29:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,也许你可以许愿让他回来\N{\rEng}Perhaps you could wish for him back.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.04,0:29:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,噢，不不不不\N{\rEng}Oh, no, no, no. No, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.35,0:29:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,不\N{\rEng}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.53,0:29:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,我…我本以为\N{\rEng}I... I thought, um,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.27,0:30:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,我可能会因为失去和背叛而悲伤，但事实上\N{\rEng}I might grieve a loss and betrayal, but, uh,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.40,0:30:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,不，我是自由的\N{\rEng}no, in fact, I was free.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.49,0:30:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,我就像一个从地牢\N{\rEng}I was like a prisoner
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.84,0:30:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,走到阳光下的囚犯\N{\rEng}emerging from a dungeon into the sunlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.46,0:30:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,我拓展了自己的生活空间\N{\rEng}I expanded into the space of my own life.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.29,0:30:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,不，我不能要求更多了\N{\rEng}No, I could not wish for more.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.46,0:30:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,你是个聪明又谨慎的女人，Alithea\N{\rEng}You are a wise and cautious woman, Alithea.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.47,0:30:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,但我们都有欲望\N{\rEng}But we all have desires,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.12,0:30:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,即使它们一直隐藏着\N{\rEng}even if they remain hidden from us.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.13,0:30:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,那也只是也许而已\N{\rEng}That's as maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.95,0:30:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,但我也是一个叙事学家\N{\rEng}But I am also a narratologist,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.87,0:30:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,这将是一个问题\N{\rEng}and that is going to be a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.35,0:30:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,这将是一个非常大的问题\N{\rEng}It's going to be a very big problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.62,0:30:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,你看，我知道所有\N{\rEng}See, I know all the stories there are
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.84,0:30:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,关于诡计多端的精灵的故事\N{\rEng}about trickster djinn,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.18,0:30:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,以及他们为自己的目的\N{\rEng}and the ways in which they manipulate wishing
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.49,0:30:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,操纵愿望的方式\N{\rEng}to their own ends.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.58,0:30:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,我不是其中之一\N{\rEng}I am not one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.88,0:30:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,我敬畏神，尊敬神\N{\rEng}I am god-fearing and honorable,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.84,0:30:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,只为满足你内心的愿望\N{\rEng}and only here to grant your heart's desire.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.11,0:30:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧，即使这是真的\N{\rEng}Well, even if that's true,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.19,0:30:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,你怎么能依靠那些被召唤的人去许愿？\N{\rEng}how can you rely on those called upon to wish?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.42,0:31:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,你怎么知道你可以依靠我？\N{\rEng}How do you know you can rely on me?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.33,0:31:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,嗯，我希望如此\N{\rEng}Well, I hope so.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.38,0:31:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,和你一起，我当然希望如此\N{\rEng}With you, I certainly hope so.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.21,0:31:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,有一个…\N{\rEng}There's a...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.43,0:31:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,有趣的小故事  我的意思是，你可能知道它\N{\rEng}funny little story. I mean, you probably know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.34,0:31:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,三个朋友坐着一艘小船迷失在海上\N{\rEng}Three friends lost at sea in a tiny boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.30,0:31:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,他们捞起了一条魔法鱼\N{\rEng}They pull up a magic fish,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.04,0:31:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,鱼满足了他们每个人的一个愿望\N{\rEng}who grants each of them one wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.61,0:31:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,第一个\N{\rEng}The first one,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.74,0:31:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,"我希望我在家里和我的妻子在一起"\N{\rEng}"I wish I were at home with my wife."
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.53,0:31:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,他消失了\N{\rEng}He vanishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.70,0:31:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,第二个，"我希望我\N{\rEng}The second one, "I wish I were playing
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.31,0:31:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,和我的孩子们在田里玩耍"\N{\rEng}"in the fields with my children."
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.62,0:31:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,他离开了\N{\rEng}Off he goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.84,0:31:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,而第三个，"我想念我的朋友…\N{\rEng}And the third one, "I miss my friends..."
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.36,0:31:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,我希望他们在这里  "\N{\rEng}"I wish they were here."
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.40,0:31:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,你已经知道了\N{\rEng}You've got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.06,0:31:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,关于许愿的故事，没有一个不是警示性的\N{\rEng}There's no story about wishing that is not a cautionary tale.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.32,0:31:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,没有一个是大团圆结局\N{\rEng}None end happily.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.24,0:31:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,甚至那些应该是笑话的也不例外\N{\rEng}Not even the ones that are supposed to be jokes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.15,0:31:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,但你和我才是这个故事的作者\N{\rEng}But you and I are the authors of this story,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.46,0:31:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,我们可以避免所有的陷阱\N{\rEng}and we can avoid all traps.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.68,0:31:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,那么，如果我根本就没有许愿呢？\N{\rEng}Well, what if I made no wish at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.03,0:31:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,抱歉？\N{\rEng}Pardon?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.69,0:31:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我没有许愿呢？\N{\rEng}What if I made no wish?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.60,0:31:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,这将是一个…\N{\rEng}That would be an...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.30,0:31:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,这将会\N{\rEng}That would be
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.56,0:32:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,灾难性的！\N{\rEng}catastrophic!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.02,0:32:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\rEng}All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.24,0:32:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我要告诉你我的接下来的监禁生涯\N{\rEng}I need to tell you about my next incarceration.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.24,0:32:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,我洗耳恭听\N{\rEng}I'm all ears.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.43,0:32:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,我永远不知道\N{\rEng}I will never know
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.17,0:32:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,我的瓶子是如何从红海之底…\N{\rEng}how my bottle came from the bottom of the Red Sea...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.35,0:32:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,到君士坦丁堡的一个宫殿\N{\rEng}...to a palace in Constantinople.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.61,0:32:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,但我认为这涉及到\N{\rEng}But I fancy somehow it involved
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.57,0:32:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,一名奥斯曼帝国战士的死亡\N{\rEng}the killing of an Ottoman warrior.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.14,0:32:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,一个帝国的灭亡\N{\rEng}The fall of an empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.11,0:33:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,还有一个恋爱中的女孩\N{\rEng}And a girl in love.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.05,0:33:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Merhaba\N{\rEng}Merhaba.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.00,0:33:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5}你是谁？
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.70,0:33:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs32\b1\bord0\shad0\c&H00002247&\pos(190,110)\fad(2200,1200)}一个精灵的遗忘
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.11,0:33:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,古腾作为奴隶\N{\rEng}Gulten lived as a slave
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.64,0:33:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,住在宫里妃嫔的\N{\rEng}in the courtyard of the concubines
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.51,0:34:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,院子里\N{\rEng}in the seraglio.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.18,0:34:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,当我出现在她面前…\N{\rEng}When I appeared to her...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.19,0:34:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,…她晕倒了\N{\rEng}...she fainted.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.36,0:34:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,我费了很大的劲才把她叫醒\N{\rEng}And I had great trouble rousing her.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.20,0:34:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,我明确表示我对她并无恶意\N{\rEng}I made it clear that I meant her no harm,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.72,0:34:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,因为我已定罪呆在这瓶子里\N{\rEng}for I was condemned to the bottle.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.55,0:34:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,直到你实现你的三个愿望\N{\rEng}Until you got your three wishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.12,0:34:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,-直到她得到她的愿望\N{\rEng}-Until she got hers.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.12,0:34:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,-拜托-好的\N{\rEng}-Please. -Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.25,0:34:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,然后，这个可怜的女孩告诉我\N{\rEng}Now, the poor girl told me
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.73,0:34:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,她疯狂地爱上了一个英俊的男人…\N{\rEng}she was distractedly in love with a beautiful man...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.17,0:34:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,她希望立即\N{\rEng}...and she wished immediately
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.65,0:34:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,得到他的好感\N{\rEng}to find favor in his eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.79,0:34:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5}我给你做了这些东西
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.97,0:35:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,碰巧的是\N{\rEng}As it happens,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.67,0:35:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,她最渴望的人是出色的穆斯塔法\N{\rEng}the one she most desired was the splendid Mustafa.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.84,0:35:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,穆斯塔法王子\N{\rEng}Prince Mustafa.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.59,0:35:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,苏莱曼大帝的长子\N{\rEng}Eldest son of Suleiman the Magnificent,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.29,0:35:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,可能是他强大王位的继承人\N{\rEng}and likely heir to his mighty throne.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.42,0:35:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我知道将要发生什么\N{\rEng}Had I known what was to come,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.86,0:35:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我会冒着伊布利斯愤怒的危险\N{\rEng}I would've risked the furies of Iblis
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.16,0:35:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,最大程度地分散她的注意力\N{\rEng}to vehemently distract her from her wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.73,0:35:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,但我不假思索\N{\rEng}But without thinking,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.39,0:35:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,拿起我的瓶子，变出油来\N{\rEng}I took my bottle and conjured oils
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.17,0:35:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,为她做准备\N{\rEng}to prepare her.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.35,0:35:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,那种曾经只有Sheba\N{\rEng}Oils of enchantment
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.92,0:35:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,使用过的魔法油\N{\rEng}once used only by Sheba.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.75,0:35:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,我告诫她要把瓶子藏起来\N{\rEng}I cautioned her to hide the bottle
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.88,0:35:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,以免它的力量落入其他人手中\N{\rEng}lest its powers fall into other hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.20,0:36:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,我去找了穆斯塔法\N{\rEng}I went to Mustafa.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.63,0:36:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Gulten\N{\rEng}Gulten.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.55,0:36:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,我轻声叫着她的名字\N{\rEng}I whispered her name.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.51,0:36:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,他派人去找她\N{\rEng}He sent for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.64,0:36:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,这太容易了\N{\rEng}It was so easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.22,0:36:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,作为一个精灵，我对人类的做事方式\N{\rEng}As a djinn, I am endlessly curious
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.44,0:36:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,有着无尽的好奇心\N{\rEng}about the ways of humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.22,0:36:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,因此，在闲暇时间\N{\rEng}So, in my spare time,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.92,0:36:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,我开始在宫殿里闲逛，寻找其中的奥秘\N{\rEng}I took to wandering the palace in search of its intrigues.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.32,0:36:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,在那里，在太监、\N{\rEng}And there, among the eunuchs,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.84,0:36:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,妃子和嫔妃中\N{\rEng}the consorts, and the concubines,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.58,0:36:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,我第一次见到胡里姆\N{\rEng}I first saw Hurrem.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.67,0:36:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,那个正在笑的人\N{\rEng}The Laughing One.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.77,0:36:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,她也是一个奴隶\N{\rEng}She, too, was a slave
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.77,0:36:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,她在他们之中崭露头角\N{\rEng}who had risen through the center of them all
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.51,0:36:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,成为苏丹的宠儿\N{\rEng}to become the Sultan's favorite.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.39,0:37:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,苏莱曼智者除了看到她之外，没有其他人\N{\rEng}Suleiman the Wise saw none but her.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.01,0:37:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,她试图保护他的王位\N{\rEng}And she sought to protect his throne
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.70,0:37:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,让自己的儿子取代他心爱的穆斯塔法\N{\rEng}in favor of her own sons over his beloved Mustafa.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.71,0:37:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,为此，她派出了许多眼线\N{\rEng}And to this end, she had the prince watched
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.93,0:37:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,盯着王子\N{\rEng}by many probing eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.81,0:37:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,当我看到Hurrem\N{\rEng}When I saw how Hurrem
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.38,0:37:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,如何成功地完成了她的杰作时\N{\rEng}made a masterpiece of her manipulations,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.38,0:37:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,我担心我的Gulten可能会被困在这张关系网里\N{\rEng}I worried that my Gulten might be caught in this web.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.26,0:37:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,我试着警告她要小心\N{\rEng}I tried to warn her to be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.31,0:37:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,但她已经决定了第二个愿望\N{\rEng}But she had already decided on her second wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.00,0:37:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5}我许愿怀孕
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.00,0:38:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5}穆斯塔法的？别这样
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.00,0:38:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5}我心意已决，满足我的愿望
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.30,0:38:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5}马上
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.00,0:38:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5}请等等
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.46,0:38:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,错得离谱\N{\rEng}Such a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.55,0:38:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,因为在这一刻\N{\rEng}Because at this moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.68,0:38:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,苏莱曼，这个神眷之人\N{\rEng}Suleiman, blessed be his name,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.94,0:38:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,正在被逐渐削弱\N{\rEng}is being undermined.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.90,0:38:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,他的战士们认为他正在变得软弱\N{\rEng}His warriors believe he is going soft,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.60,0:38:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,他对他的诗歌更感兴趣\N{\rEng}more interested in his poetry
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.34,0:38:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,而不是铁腕统治\N{\rEng}than ruling with a strong hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.10,0:38:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,胡勒姆助长了\N{\rEng}Hurrem fuels the rumors
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.06,0:38:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,军方想要夺取他的王位\N{\rEng}that the military want to take his throne
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.06,0:38:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,用穆斯塔法取代他的谣言\N{\rEng}and replace him with Mustafa.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.76,0:38:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,这位王子成了无休止的\N{\rEng}The prince has become a pawn
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.41,0:38:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,权力游戏中的一枚棋子\N{\rEng}in the ceaseless game of power.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.64,0:39:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,伟大的苏莱曼\N{\rEng}Suleiman the Magnificent,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.73,0:39:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,征服者苏莱曼\N{\rEng}Suleiman the Conqueror,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.47,0:39:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,帝国的保护者和保护者\N{\rEng}patron and protector of empires,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.35,0:39:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,父亲苏莱曼\N{\rEng}Suleiman the Father,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.87,0:39:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,面临着一个\N{\rEng}was left with a choice
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.39,0:39:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,他知道会让他心碎的选择\N{\rEng}that he knows will break his heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.49,0:39:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,与此同时，古腾认为\N{\rEng}Gulten, meantime, saw no reason
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.45,0:39:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,没有理由不让她露面\N{\rEng}why she should remain unseen.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.54,0:39:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,鉴于她怀的是下一任苏丹的儿子\N{\rEng}Given she was carrying the son of the next Sultan.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.55,0:39:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,她不顾我所有的警告\N{\rEng}Despite all my warnings,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.69,0:39:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,炫耀着自己刚刚隆起的胸部和腹部\N{\rEng}she parades her newly swollen breasts and belly.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.73,0:39:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,风声很快传遍了整个宫廷\N{\rEng}And the whispers soon spread throughout the seraglio.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.57,0:40:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,可怕的阴谋进展得太快了\N{\rEng}The terrible plottings move all too quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.99,0:40:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,穆斯塔法王子天真地\N{\rEng}Prince Mustafa comes innocently
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.47,0:40:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,来到父亲面前\N{\rEng}into the presence of his father,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.69,0:40:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,向父亲保证自己的忠诚\N{\rEng}to reassure him of his loyalty.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.00,0:40:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5}苏丹陛下
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.00,0:40:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5}父王
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.44,0:40:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,而缄默者正在等待他\N{\rEng}And the mutes are waiting for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.67,0:40:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,他向爱戴他的\N{\rEng}He cried out to his Janissaries,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.63,0:41:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,禁卫军士兵呼救\N{\rEng}who loved him,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.24,0:41:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,但他的声音被他父亲的弓弦压碎了\N{\rEng}but his voice was crushed and his breath stopped
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.98,0:41:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,他的呼吸也停止了\N{\rEng}by the string of his father's bow.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.00,0:41:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,-Gulten！\N{\rEng}-Gulten!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.87,0:41:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5}他们来抓你了！
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.00,0:41:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5}快许愿！
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.00,0:41:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5}只要再许一个愿！
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.00,0:41:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5}为什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.00,0:41:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5}他们正赶过来杀你！
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.00,0:41:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5}王子会保护我的！
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.00,0:41:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5}他什么都做不了了
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.40,0:41:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5}快许愿，许愿！
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.20,0:41:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5}他爱我
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.00,0:41:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5}他死了！
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.88,0:41:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5}爱护他的人都死了！
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.00,0:41:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5}Hurrem来找你了
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.99,0:42:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,许愿！\N{\rEng}"Make a wish!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.56,0:42:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,救你自己,Gulten ！\N{\rEng}"Save yourself, Gulten!"
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.13,0:42:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,只需要几句话，她就可以\N{\rEng}Just a few words and she could have been free
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.87,0:42:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,安全地生下她的孩子\N{\rEng}to bear her child in safety,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.57,0:42:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,而我也终于可以魂归精灵界了\N{\rEng}and I to spirit away at last to the Realm of Djinn.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.14,0:42:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,但她跑到了刺客的手里\N{\rEng}But she ran into the hands of the assassins.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.23,0:42:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,我正准备用武力救回他们\N{\rEng}I was about to take them by force,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.58,0:42:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,却被伊比利斯的一个追随者挡住了\N{\rEng}when I was blocked by a follower of Iblis.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.00,0:42:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5\c&H0000C2CD&}这里不欢迎你
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.00,0:42:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5\c&H0000C2CD&}你无法改变她的故事
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.00,0:42:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5\c&H0000C2CD&}如果她不许愿，你就完蛋了
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.23,0:43:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Gulten！\N{\rEng}Gulten!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.64,0:43:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,她没有许下要拯救自己的愿望\N{\rEng}She made no wish to save herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.95,0:43:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,没有为拯救我们俩而许愿\N{\rEng}No wish was made to save us both.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.14,0:43:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,所以，我在那里\N{\rEng}So, there I was,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.18,0:43:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,或者说我不在那里，你也可以说\N{\rEng}or there I was not, might you say,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.27,0:43:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,我差点就被解放了，结果我被一个未完成的第三个愿望\N{\rEng}almost emancipated and tethered to this world
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.36,0:43:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,拴在这个世界上\N{\rEng}by a third wish unperformed.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.93,0:43:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,但你意识到了，对吧？\N{\rEng}But you realize, don't you,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.58,0:43:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,你刚刚给我讲了一个女人因为自己的愿望\N{\rEng}that you've just told me the story of a woman who was doomed
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.41,0:43:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,而注定要失败的故事？\N{\rEng}as a consequence of the wishes she made?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.67,0:44:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,是的，但她没有完成的愿望\N{\rEng}Yes, but her failure to complete the wishes
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.33,0:44:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,也注定了我的失败\N{\rEng}also doomed me.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.64,0:44:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,没有人可以完成这个愿望吗？\N{\rEng}Could nobody else complete the wish?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.77,0:44:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,这是我的希望\N{\rEng}That was my hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.34,0:44:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,最终这将解放你？\N{\rEng}And that would finally liberate you?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.21,0:44:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,这是我唯一的希望\N{\rEng}That was my only hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.86,0:44:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,但是，你却被弄得消失了\N{\rEng}But you were rendered invisible.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.04,0:44:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,像个幽灵一样\N{\rEng}Like a ghost.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.13,0:44:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,徘徊在看不见的地方\N{\rEng}Wandering unseen.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.95,0:44:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,而你的瓶子\N{\rEng}And your bottle,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.22,0:44:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,藏在松动的石头下\N{\rEng}hidden under the loosened stone
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.17,0:44:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,只有死去的Gulten知道\N{\rEng}known only to the dead Gulten.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.74,0:44:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,是的，我被困在那了\N{\rEng}Yes, it was a predicament.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.22,0:44:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,我试图吸引人们的注意\N{\rEng}I tried to attract the attention of someone,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.70,0:44:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,任何能帮助我的人都行\N{\rEng}anyone that could help me.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.71,0:44:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,我的天啊，我那么努力\N{\rEng}My stars, how I tried.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.36,0:44:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,我追踪他们的气味，追踪他们的每一步\N{\rEng}I followed their scent, their every step.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.93,0:44:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,愿意,恳求,尖叫\N{\rEng}Willing, pleading, screaming.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.15,0:44:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,只要能把他们吸引过来\N{\rEng}Anything to draw them to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.14,0:45:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我就这样可怜兮兮地做了100年\N{\rEng}And I do this piteously for 100 years,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.83,0:45:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,每一次失败，我的意志就开始消退\N{\rEng}and with every failure, my will begins to fade.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.71,0:45:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,然后在1620年\N{\rEng}And then in 1620,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.85,0:45:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,希望终于出现  一个持剑的男孩现身了\N{\rEng}hope comes in the form of a boy with a sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.10,0:45:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs32\b1\bord0\shad0\c&H00002247&\pos(190,100)\fad(600,1200)}两兄弟和女巨人
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.34,0:45:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Murad！ Murad！\N{\rEng}Murad! Murad!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.39,0:45:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Murad！\N{\rEng}Murad!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.40,0:46:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,通过某种方式，这个男孩感觉到了我\N{\rEng}By some means, this boy senses me.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.28,0:46:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,我能够把他吸引到石头上\N{\rEng}I'm able to draw him to the stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.29,0:46:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Ibrahim！\N{\rEng}Ibrahim!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.98,0:46:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Gel\N{\rEng}Gel.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.29,0:47:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Murad！\N{\rEng}Murad!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.86,0:47:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Ibrahim！\N{\rEng}Ibrahim!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.51,0:47:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,就在我即将\N{\rEng}And just as I am about to be delivered
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.12,0:47:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,到达他们手中的时候\N{\rEng}into their hands,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.43,0:47:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,他们的母亲找到了他们\N{\rEng}their mother finds them.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.30,0:47:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,她是Kosem\N{\rEng}She is Kosem,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.96,0:47:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,苏丹艾哈迈德一世的遗孀\N{\rEng}a widow of the Sultan, Ahmed the First.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.18,0:47:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,而男孩们则是王位的下一个继承者\N{\rEng}And the boys are next in line for the throne.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.40,0:47:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,当我看到他腿上的毛发\N{\rEng}When I see the hair on his legs,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.84,0:47:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道，在穆拉德的血脉某处\N{\rEng}I know that somewhere in Murad's bloodline
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.58,0:47:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,涌动着精灵的力量\N{\rEng}pulses the power of a djinn.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.49,0:47:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,我到处跟着他\N{\rEng}I follow him everywhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.28,0:47:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,决心把他拉回到石头上\N{\rEng}determined to draw him back to the stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.85,0:47:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,但在11岁时，他就登上了王位\N{\rEng}But at the age of 11, he ascends the throne
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.89,0:47:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,成为穆拉德第四苏丹\N{\rEng}and becomes Sultan Murad the Fourth.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.98,0:47:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,他又陷入了惯常的阴谋诡计\N{\rEng}And caught up by the usual intrigues,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.98,0:47:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,他对我来说更加迷茫\N{\rEng}he is even more lost to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.29,0:47:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,20岁时，他带领他的军队去打仗\N{\rEng}At 20, he leads his armies to war.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.25,0:47:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,他与他的手下\N{\rEng}He battles alongside his men
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.99,0:47:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,在高加索和美索不达米亚并肩作战\N{\rEng}in the Caucasus and Mesopotamia.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.52,0:47:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,关于他鲁莽的故事传得到处都是\N{\rEng}Stories are told of his recklessness,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.95,0:47:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,甚至伴随了他一生\N{\rEng}even with his own life.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.35,0:48:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,再一次，我对见到他这事感到绝望\N{\rEng}I despair of ever seeing him again.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.62,0:48:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,“希望”是一个怪物，Alithea，而我是它的玩物\N{\rEng}Hope is a monster, Alithea, and I am its plaything.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.58,0:48:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,所以他死了吗？\N{\rEng}So he died?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.97,0:48:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,不是在战场上\N{\rEng}Not in battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.93,0:48:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,回到伊斯坦布尔\N{\rEng}Back in Istanbul,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.19,0:48:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,科瑟姆需要保护王位\N{\rEng}Kosem needs to protect the throne.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.33,0:48:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,她需要保护易卜拉欣\N{\rEng}She needs to protect Ibrahim.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.15,0:48:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,—小弟弟吗?  -是的\N{\rEng}-The little brother? -Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.55,0:48:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,他是奥斯曼家族的独苗\N{\rEng}He is last of the Ottoman line.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.95,0:48:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,他必须生男孩\N{\rEng}He has to produce male children.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.91,0:48:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,所以，科瑟姆把他锁在一个铁笼里，铁笼里全是黑貂皮\N{\rEng}So, Kosem locks him in a cage lined entirely with sable.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.96,0:48:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,相当于监狱\N{\rEng}Quite the prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.57,0:48:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,而且是一个他永远不想离开的地方\N{\rEng}And one he will never want to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.50,0:49:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,这让他大为放荡\N{\rEng}It debauches him royally.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.94,0:49:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,他认为肉体的面积越大\N{\rEng}He believes the greater the expanse of flesh,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.60,0:49:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,快感就越强烈\N{\rEng}the more intense the pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.29,0:49:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,因此，科塞姆寻找丰满而巨大的美女\N{\rEng}So, Kosem seeks out beauties voluptuous and immense,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.25,0:49:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,并把她们带到他的沙发上\N{\rEng}and brings them to his couch.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.47,0:49:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,我的命运完全取决于这个恋物癖\N{\rEng}My fate turns specifically on this fetish.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.48,0:49:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,这是怎么回事？\N{\rEng}How's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.61,0:49:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,你会明白的\N{\rEng}You'll see.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.47,0:50:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,穆拉德回来了\N{\rEng}Murad is back.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.30,0:50:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,虽然他回来时是个征服者\N{\rEng}And though he returns a conqueror,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.17,0:50:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,但他已经不能脱下他的染血战袍\N{\rEng}he cannot shed his robes of blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.78,0:50:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,战争已经真正腐化了他的灵魂\N{\rEng}War had truly rotted his soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.37,0:50:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我等待着，直到他独自一人\N{\rEng}I wait until he is alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.24,0:50:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,我决心把他引回石头上\N{\rEng}I am determined to draw him back to the stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.42,0:50:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,我不想打断你，但我确实有一个问题\N{\rEng}I don't want to interrupt, but I do have a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.59,0:50:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,对你来说，这样的人\N{\rEng}Did it matter to you what kind of wish
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.64,0:50:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,可能会许下什么样的愿望很重要吗？\N{\rEng}such a man might make?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.64,0:50:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,一个如此贪得无厌的人\N{\rEng}One so insatiable.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.51,0:50:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,不重要\N{\rEng}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.34,0:50:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,即使是极度邪恶也不重要？\N{\rEng}Not even if it were profoundly evil?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.30,0:50:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,如果这意味着我的自由，也不重要\N{\rEng}Not if it meant my freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.82,0:50:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,事实是他有其他事情要做\N{\rEng}The truth is he has other things on his mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.35,0:50:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,他相信自己是无敌的\N{\rEng}He believes he is invincible,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.66,0:51:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,要想无限期地统治，他必须除掉所有的对手\N{\rEng}and to rule indefinitely, he must be rid of all rivals.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.55,0:51:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5}为什么要浪费你的剑，我的雄狮
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.11,0:51:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Ibrahim\N{\rEng}Ibrahim.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.50,0:51:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Ibrahim\N{\rEng}Ibrahim.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.72,0:51:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5}大哥
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.30,0:52:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5}他只是个孩子，他怎么可能有能力统治？
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.61,0:52:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,科瑟姆必须阻止他\N{\rEng}Kosem needs to stop him.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.92,0:52:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,无论如何，她需要用其他乐子\N{\rEng}Somehow, she needed to distract him
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.18,0:52:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,来转移他的嗜血欲望\N{\rEng}from his bloodlust with other gratifications.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.93,0:52:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,首先，她安排他一直醉醺醺的\N{\rEng}First, she arranges for him to be perpetually drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.28,0:52:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,然后她做了件非常精明的事\N{\rEng}And then she tries something very shrewd.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.20,0:52:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,你可能会喜欢的事\N{\rEng}Something that you might enjoy.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.81,0:52:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,她派人\N{\rEng}She sends to find,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.29,0:52:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,从帝国的各个角落\N{\rEng}from all corners of the empire,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.47,0:52:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,寻找最会讲故事的人\N{\rEng}the best storytellers.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.84,0:53:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,那些没有口才的人在恐惧中逃跑\N{\rEng}Those who are not persuasive
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.97,0:53:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,或者倒在他的不耐烦中\N{\rEng}flee in fear or fall to his impatience.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.55,0:53:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,只有一个人\N{\rEng}There is only one
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.33,0:53:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,有能力使他着迷\N{\rEng}who has the ability to enchant him.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.25,0:53:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,用故事来抚慰他\N{\rEng}To soothe with stories,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.60,0:53:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,让他被故事的展开深深吸引\N{\rEng}to hold him hostage to their unfolding.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.02,0:54:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,这是他唯一的朋友\N{\rEng}This is his only friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.54,0:54:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,然后友谊就变成了爱情\N{\rEng}And that friendship turns to love.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.55,0:54:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,因为我没有别的事可做\N{\rEng}Since there is nothing else for me to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.68,0:54:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我满怀感激地听着\N{\rEng}I listen gratefully,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.20,0:54:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,因为我也喜欢沉浸在他的故事里\N{\rEng}for I, too, love being lost in his stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.69,0:54:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,老人死后\N{\rEng}When the old man dies,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.65,0:54:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,王宫里的人都逃到街上\N{\rEng}all in the palace flee to the streets,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.00,0:54:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,因为他们担心穆拉德的悲痛会招致新的屠杀\N{\rEng}for they fear Murad's grief will incur fresh murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.57,0:54:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,但他只是坐着，嚎叫着，一直喝酒，直到喝空为止\N{\rEng}But he just sits, and howls, and drinks until he is empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.78,0:55:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,而我的耐心得到了回报\N{\rEng}And my patience is rewarded.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.56,0:55:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,因为在这种状态下\N{\rEng}For in this state,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.00,0:55:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,我终于能够引起他的注意\N{\rEng}I am finally able to get his attention
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.35,0:55:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,并把他引回那个隐秘的浴室\N{\rEng}and draw him back to the secret bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.31,0:55:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,哦，我知道接下来会发生什么\N{\rEng}Oh, I know where this is going.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.88,0:55:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,他将会太虚弱，无法举起石头\N{\rEng}He's going to be too weak to lift the stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.49,0:55:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,甚至连转动门闩都不行\N{\rEng}Too weak even to turn the latch.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.71,0:55:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,于是，他离开了，喝得酩酊大醉，永远睡不着觉\N{\rEng}So, he leaves and drinks himself to permanent sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.63,0:55:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh！\N{\rEng}Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.93,0:55:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,而我就只能在那里\N{\rEng}And there I am,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.72,0:55:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,被人遗忘\N{\rEng}left to my own oblivion,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.07,0:55:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,没有人听到我的声音\N{\rEng}with no one to hear my voice,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.59,0:55:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,没有人认识我，没有人感觉得到我，更没有人感知我\N{\rEng}no one to know me, nor feel me, nor sense me.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.94,0:55:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,你无法想象\N{\rEng}You can't imagine.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.38,0:55:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,嗯，实际上，我可以\N{\rEng}Well, actually, I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.34,0:55:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,你能想象那种孤独感吗？\N{\rEng}Can you imagine the loneliness?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.56,0:55:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,怎样才能击垮它？\N{\rEng}How it might overwhelm?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.83,0:55:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我可以\N{\rEng}I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.83,0:56:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,只有当我们对别人来说是真实的，我们才会存在\N{\rEng}We exist only if we are real to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.48,0:56:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,你同意吗？\N{\rEng}Do you agree?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.66,0:56:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我同意\N{\rEng}I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.92,0:56:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是我们的命运，Alithea\N{\rEng}This, then, is our fate, Alithea.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.58,0:56:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你根本不许愿\N{\rEng}If you make no wish at all,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.71,0:56:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,我就会被困在两个世界之间\N{\rEng}I will be caught between worlds,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.45,0:56:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,永远隐形，永远孤独\N{\rEng}invisible and alone, for all of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.85,0:56:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,许个愿吧, Alithea\N{\rEng}Make a wish, Alithea.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.46,0:56:21.37,Default,,0,0,0,,让它成为你的心愿\N{\rEng}Make it your heart's desire.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.16,0:56:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我是你，我会更加小心\N{\rEng}I'd be more careful if I were you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.17,0:56:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,很明显，你想办法找到了应对之法\N{\rEng}Obviously, you managed to find your way out.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.43,0:56:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,或多或少有点\N{\rEng}More or less.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.69,0:56:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,我一开始认为我是在一个\N{\rEng}I'm beginning to think I'm in the presence
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.04,0:56:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,诡计多端的人面前\N{\rEng}of a trickster.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.04,0:56:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,如果是那样就好了\N{\rEng}That would be so much better.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.70,0:56:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,我的工作会轻松很多\N{\rEng}My work would be so much easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.57,0:56:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,但事实是，我只是个\N{\rEng}But the truth is, I am just an idiot
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.44,0:56:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,运气差得离谱的白痴\N{\rEng}who has been extravagantly unlucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.05,0:56:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧，我不得不相信你的话\N{\rEng}Well, I have to take your word for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.72,0:57:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,那么？\N{\rEng}So?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.68,0:57:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我想，Ibrahim, 最后成为了苏丹吧？\N{\rEng}Ibrahim, I suppose, becomes Sultan?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.07,0:57:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Ibrahim, 必须被拖到王位上\N{\rEng}Ibrahim has to be dragged to the throne.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.71,0:57:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,他任命他的一个嫔妃\N{\rEng}He appoints one of his concubines
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.75,0:57:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,成为大马士革的总督\N{\rEng}Governor of Damascus.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.49,0:57:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,她的名字叫Sugar Lump（糖块）\N{\rEng}Her name is Sugar Lump.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.02,0:57:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,无论从哪个角度看，都是他的最爱\N{\rEng}By every measure, his favorite.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.11,0:57:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,如果她不是到处溜达的话\N{\rEng}Had she not been free to roam,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.02,0:57:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,她就不会发现那个秘密浴室\N{\rEng}she would not have found the secret bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.94,0:57:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,要不是她决定去洗澡\N{\rEng}Had she not decided to take a bath,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.16,0:57:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,水就不会灌满了\N{\rEng}it would not have overfilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.64,0:57:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,如果她在地板上走的时候\N{\rEng}Had she not been clumsy
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.94,0:57:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,不是笨手笨脚的话\N{\rEng}as she walked across the floor,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.55,0:57:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,她就不会滑倒，摔碎石头\N{\rEng}she would not have slipped, smashed the stone,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.82,0:58:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,-然后找到我的瓶子  -啊，是的\N{\rEng}-and found my bottle. -Ah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.71,0:58:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,说实话，我应该更有尊严一些\N{\rEng}To be honest, I should have been more dignified.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.97,0:58:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,但我开始乞求，无耻地乞求\N{\rEng}But I began to beg, shamelessly.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.25,0:58:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5}求求你，好心的女士，我的情况很糟糕
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.10,0:58:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5}已经迫在眉睫了，你得帮我
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.00,0:58:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5}你可以许愿，任何愿望都可以
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.00,0:58:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5}我不想与邪恶的精灵有任何关系
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.50,0:58:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5}你有什么想要的吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.00,0:58:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5}一定有的，许愿吧！说出来！告诉我！现在就说！快！
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.57,0:58:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,我希望你回到\N{\rEng}"I wish you were back
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.05,0:58:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,你在博斯普鲁斯海峡底的瓶子里  "\N{\rEng}" in your bottle at the bottom of the Bosphorus."
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.01,0:59:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我在这里\N{\rEng}So here I am,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.31,0:59:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,落入了你小心翼翼的手中\N{\rEng}fallen into your careful hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.28,0:59:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,似乎我们无法逃避对方\N{\rEng}Seems we cannot escape each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.23,0:59:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,你让我听从你的摆布\N{\rEng}You have me at your mercy.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.94,0:59:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,这种许愿…\N{\rEng}This wishing...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.90,0:59:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,是一种危险的艺术\N{\rEng}It's a hazardous art.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.03,0:59:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,"我希望 "会带来无尽的解脱\N{\rEng}"I wish" brings infinite unravelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.86,0:59:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,不一定\N{\rEng}Not necessarily.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.99,0:59:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,嗯，在你所有的故事里都有\N{\rEng}Well, it's there in all your own stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.04,0:59:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道,但是…\N{\rEng}I know, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.12,0:59:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,你说你不是骗子\N{\rEng}You say you're not a trickster,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.73,0:59:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,你还说你和我是这个故事的作者\N{\rEng}and you say that you and I are the authors of this story.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.13,0:59:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,但我无法把自己写出来\N{\rEng}But I'm not able to write myself out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.18,0:59:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,对\N{\rEng}Correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.44,0:59:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,你为什么不跳回你的瓶子里\N{\rEng}Why don't you just hop back into your bottle
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.18,0:59:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我就把它交给更容易受骗的人呢？\N{\rEng}and I'll give it to someone more gullible?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.92,0:59:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,更绝望的人，更贪婪的人\N{\rEng}Someone more desperate. Someone more greedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.88,0:59:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,我不会再回到瓶子里了\N{\rEng}I'm not getting back in the bottle.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.06,0:59:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么？\N{\rEng}Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.14,0:59:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,我不会再回到瓶子里了\N{\rEng}I'm not getting back in the bottle.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.97,0:59:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧，我不是在提出三个愿望\N{\rEng}Well, I am not making three wishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.97,0:59:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,那你就是在把我送进湮没的深渊\N{\rEng}Then you are sending me to my oblivion.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.15,0:59:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,噢，你真难对付\N{\rEng}Oh, you're impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.63,0:59:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,你让我感到头疼\N{\rEng}And you are giving me a headache.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.63,0:59:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧，好吧\N{\rEng}All right. All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.33,1:00:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,我将这样做  我将提出三个愿望\N{\rEng}Here's what I'll do. I will make three wishes.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.90,1:00:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,-我会  -在你死之前？\N{\rEng}-I will. -Before you die?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.03,1:00:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,是现在  一个接一个\N{\rEng}Right now. One after the other.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.81,1:00:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,-准备好了吗？  -嗯，嗯\N{\rEng}-Ready? -Mmm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.03,1:00:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,第一  我希望你的头痛消失\N{\rEng}Number one. I wish your headache were gone.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.73,1:00:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,第二\N{\rEng}Number two.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.34,1:00:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我希望能喝上一口这种茶\N{\rEng}I wish for a sip of this tea.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.74,1:00:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,最后，我希望再来一个这个\N{\rEng}And finally, I wish for another one of those.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.79,1:00:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,你耍我\N{\rEng}You mock me.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.13,1:00:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,三个愿望，非常简单\N{\rEng}Three wishes, perfectly simple,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.83,1:00:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,而且理论上是安全的\N{\rEng}and theoretically safe.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.96,1:00:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,我被所罗门囚禁\N{\rEng}I was imprisoned by Solomon precisely
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.05,1:00:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,正是因为我喊出了我内心的愿望\N{\rEng}because I cried out my heart's desire.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.71,1:00:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,只有答应你的要求，我才能重获自由\N{\rEng}Only by granting you yours may I earn my release.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.62,1:00:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,是的，好吧，我很欣赏这种对等\N{\rEng}Yes, well, I appreciate the symmetry,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.06,1:00:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,但问题是\N{\rEng}but the thing is this,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.63,1:00:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,我这辈子都提不出一个合适的愿望\N{\rEng}I cannot for the life of me summon up one eligible wish.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.41,1:00:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,而你还要我给你三个\N{\rEng}And you're asking me for three.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.89,1:00:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,你身上还有没有生命力？你还活着吗？\N{\rEng}Is there any life in you? Are you even alive?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.15,1:00:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,知道吗，在某些文化中\N{\rEng}You know, in some cultures,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.98,1:00:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,没有欲望就意味着开悟\N{\rEng}absence of desire means enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.72,1:00:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,那么你就是一个虔诚的傻瓜\N{\rEng}Then you are a pious fool.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.94,1:00:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我很满足，为什么还要去冒险？\N{\rEng}If I'm content, why tempt fate?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.21,1:00:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,而你是个懦夫\N{\rEng}And you're a coward.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.64,1:00:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,别刺激我\N{\rEng}Don't goad me.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.99,1:00:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,无论是人类、天使还是精灵\N{\rEng}There is no human, no angel, nor djinn
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.95,1:00:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,都不会不抓住这个机会\N{\rEng}that wouldn't grasp at the chance
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.21,1:00:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,来满足他们内心深处的渴望\N{\rEng}to fulfill their deepest longings,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.87,1:00:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,而我却得搞定一个声称\N{\rEng}and I am saddled with the one
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.35,1:00:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,什么都不想要的人\N{\rEng}who claims to want nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.87,1:01:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Alithea Binnie,你是个骗子！\N{\rEng}Alithea Binnie, you are a liar!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.39,1:01:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道，我开始希望我们从未见过面\N{\rEng}You know, I am beginning to wish we never met.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.70,1:01:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,不！不！不！\N{\rEng}No! Nyet!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.01,1:01:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,别这么说！\N{\rEng}Don't say that!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.25,1:01:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,那么\N{\rEng}So...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.87,1:01:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,这事以前就在你身上发生过\N{\rEng}that's happened to you before.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.35,1:01:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,那太糟了\N{\rEng}And it was bad.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.22,1:01:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,是很糟糕\N{\rEng}'Twas bad.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.40,1:01:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,太苦了\N{\rEng}'Twas bitter.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.44,1:01:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,这是最残酷的愿望\N{\rEng}'Twas the cruelest wish of all.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.79,1:01:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,你又一次被愚蠢的行为毁了\N{\rEng}You were undone by silliness yet again.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.15,1:02:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,我在这里是因为一个天才\N{\rEng}I'm here because of a genius.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.15,1:02:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,这次是又谁？\N{\rEng}Who was it this time?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.98,1:02:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,她是Zefir\N{\rEng}She was Zefir.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.50,1:02:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,在人类中很少有这样的奇迹\N{\rEng}Rarely among humankind has there been such a wonder.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.46,1:02:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,但你在这里是因为她的愚蠢\N{\rEng}But you're here because of her folly.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.34,1:02:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,我是由于Zefir的缘故才落得如此下场\N{\rEng}I ended up in this as a consequence of Zefir.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.39,1:02:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,而这就是你一直以来\N{\rEng}And this is the story
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.78,1:02:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,都在避免告诉我的故事\N{\rEng}you've been avoiding telling me all along.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.05,1:02:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,这个故事我连自己都不想讲\N{\rEng}This is the story I've avoided telling even myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:46.54,1:02:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Zefir是一个弃儿\N{\rEng}Zefir was a foundling,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.93,1:02:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,12岁时嫁给了一个富有的商人\N{\rEng}married at 12 to a wealthy merchant.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.11,1:02:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,他比她大得多，而且很善良\N{\rEng}He was much older than her, and kind,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.33,1:03:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你认为把一个人像鸟一样关在笼子里是善良的话\N{\rEng}if you think keeping someone like a bird in a cage is kind.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.82,1:03:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,家里还有两个年长的妻子，她们不喜欢她\N{\rEng}There were two older wives, who did not like her
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.47,1:03:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,根本不和她说话\N{\rEng}and did not talk to her at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.23,1:03:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,每个人，包括仆人\N{\rEng}Everyone, including the servants,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.14,1:03:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,似乎都在嘲笑她\N{\rEng}seemed to be mocking her.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.99,1:03:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,她既不懂礼仪，也不懂学问\N{\rEng}She had neither etiquette nor learning.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.08,1:03:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,她长得不怎么漂亮\N{\rEng}She grew to no great beauty
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.99,1:03:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,不知为什么就生气了\N{\rEng}and was angry without knowing why.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.31,1:04:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,就像命运安排的那样\N{\rEng}As the fates would have it, my bottle came to her
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.18,1:04:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,我的瓶子作为她丈夫爱的信物送给了她\N{\rEng}as a love token from her husband.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:13.58,1:04:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,当她满足了他\N{\rEng}And when she had finished satisfying him
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.63,1:04:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,终于独自一人\N{\rEng}and was finally alone,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.11,1:04:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,她设法撬开了瓶子\N{\rEng}she managed to prise it open.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.40,1:04:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,她好像一直在等我\N{\rEng}It was as if she was waiting for me.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.06,1:04:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,我一眼就看出她很机灵\N{\rEng}I saw at once that she was sharp,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.19,1:05:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,她也看出我渴望\N{\rEng}and she saw that I was desperate
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.07,1:05:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,自由和交谈\N{\rEng}for freedom and conversation.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.29,1:05:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,我把我给你说的那些故事都告诉了她\N{\rEng}I told her my story, as I have told you,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.03,1:05:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,她通过她所做的东西向我展示了自己\N{\rEng}and she revealed herself to me by the things she had made.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.29,1:05:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Gel  Gel\N{\rEng}Gel. Gel.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.50,1:05:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Gel\N{\rEng}Gel.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.60,1:06:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,她本可以像天才达芬奇\N{\rEng}She could have been remembered
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.34,1:06:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,一样被人们记住\N{\rEng}like the genius da Vinci,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.26,1:06:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,她的飞行理论\N{\rEng}whose theories on flight
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.65,1:06:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,是苏丹和国王们的谈资\N{\rEng}were the talk of sultans and kings.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.09,1:06:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,她是一位技艺高超的艺术家，但没人看过她的作品\N{\rEng}She was a skilled artist, but no one saw her art.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.58,1:06:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,她告诉我她被还未使用过的能量\N{\rEng}She told me she was eaten up
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.28,1:06:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,吞噬了\N{\rEng}with unused power.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.50,1:06:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,她觉得自己可能是个女巫\N{\rEng}She thought she might be a witch.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.41,1:06:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,不过，她说，如果她是个男人\N{\rEng}Except, she said, if she were a man,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.28,1:06:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,她的才智会被广泛接受\N{\rEng}her intellect would have been ordinarily accepted.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.11,1:06:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,她是一个渴望学习的女人\N{\rEng}She was a woman ardent for learning,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.46,1:06:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,于是我知道了她的第一个愿望是什么\N{\rEng}and I knew what her first wish would be.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.11,1:06:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5}我想要知识
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.00,1:06:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\b0\bord0\shad1.5}我希望获得一切有用的，美丽的和真实的知识
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.31,1:06:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我很高兴\N{\rEng}And it delighted me
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.75,1:06:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,能实现这个愿望\N{\rEng}to fulfill this wish.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.69,1:07:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,所以，我教她历史，哲学\N{\rEng}So, I taught her histories, philosophies,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.26,1:07:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,语言，诗歌\N{\rEng}languages, poetry.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.70,1:07:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,我教她天文学，数学\N{\rEng}I taught her astronomy, mathematic,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.35,1:07:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,这对她来说是莫大的幸福\N{\rEng}which was bliss to her.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.53,1:07:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,我给她带来了书和文章\N{\rEng}I brought her books and writings,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.09,1:07:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,我们把它们藏在她收藏的瓶子里\N{\rEng}which we hid in her collection of bottles.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.86,1:08:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Sabah…\N{\rEng}Sabah...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.86,1:08:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Sabah…\N{\rEng}Sabah...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.23,1:08:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,她总是可以从一个红色的玻璃罐里\N{\rEng}She could always call on Aristotle
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.27,1:08:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,找到亚里士多德\N{\rEng}from a red glass jar,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.45,1:08:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,从一个绿色的玻璃罐找到欧几里得\N{\rEng}or Euclid from a green,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.23,1:08:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,毕达哥拉斯，斯宾诺莎\N{\rEng}Pythagoras, Spinoza,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.63,1:08:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,而不需要我重塑他们\N{\rEng}without needing me to re-embody them.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.73,1:08:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,她的房间里，我们拥有整个世界\N{\rEng}We had the whole world in her room,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.12,1:08:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,而我却爱上了她\N{\rEng}and I lost my heart to her.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:56.78,1:09:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,能使她幸福\N{\rEng}'Twas my bliss to make her happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.61,1:09:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,看到她的茁壮成长，是我的福气\N{\rEng}To see her flourish.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.70,1:09:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,她在各方面\N{\rEng}And she flourished in every way.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.62,1:09:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,都发展得很好\N{\rEng}Totalmente.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.24,1:09:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,她甚至开始反抗\N{\rEng}She began to rebel
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.68,1:09:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,她丈夫要求的\N{\rEng}even against the gestures of submission
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.76,1:09:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,服从姿态\N{\rEng}that her husband required,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.33,1:09:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,因为她已经掌握了一种爱的技巧\N{\rEng}for she had acquired a mastery of love-craft,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.55,1:09:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,是任何没有和精灵做爱的\N{\rEng}out of reach of any human
Dialogue: 0,1:09:31.21,1:09:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,人类所不能达到的\N{\rEng}that had not made love to a djinn.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.31,1:09:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,他对她的渴求变成了一种痴迷\N{\rEng}His cravings for her became an obsession.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.67,1:10:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,当他来找她时\N{\rEng}And when he would come to her,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.33,1:10:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,我便离开她的房间，飞向天空\N{\rEng}I would leave her room and journey the skies.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.68,1:10:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,我看到了群山、海洋…\N{\rEng}I saw the mountains, the oceans...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.38,1:10:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,我看见森林里的野兽\N{\rEng}I saw the beasts of the forest,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.38,1:10:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,那里人迹罕至\N{\rEng}where no man treads.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.95,1:10:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,当我回来的时候，她会等着我\N{\rEng}And when I would return, she would be waiting for me.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.00,1:10:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我会告诉她我这一天的经历\N{\rEng}I would tell her of my day, and she would faint with joy
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.91,1:10:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,她会因为高兴和失望而晕倒\N{\rEng}and disappointment.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.92,1:10:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,她为什么不许愿得到自由呢？\N{\rEng}Why did she not make a wish to be free?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.53,1:10:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,对她来说还有更重要的事\N{\rEng}There was something more important to her.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:36.92,1:10:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,她发明了一种“数学”语言\N{\rEng}She had devised a "mathematica,"
Dialogue: 0,1:10:39.40,1:10:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,用来解释\N{\rEng}a language to explain the forces
Dialogue: 0,1:10:42.58,1:10:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,使空间、时间和物质形成的力量\N{\rEng}which bring space, and time, and matter into being.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.71,1:10:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,她是普罗米修斯，很勇敢\N{\rEng}She was Promethean, brave.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:47.37,1:10:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,但她无法解开这个谜题\N{\rEng}But she could not solve this puzzle.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.63,1:10:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,她需要一把钥匙\N{\rEng}She needed a key,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:51.72,1:10:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,一把打开她感知之门的钥匙\N{\rEng}a key to open the doors of her perception.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.52,1:11:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,因此，她使用了她的第二个愿望\N{\rEng}So, she used her second wish.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.43,1:11:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我教她像精灵一样做梦，醒着\N{\rEng}I taught her to dream as djinn do, awake.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.69,1:11:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,就这样，她找到了答案\N{\rEng}And this way, the solutions came to her.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:48.60,1:11:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,她能解释无形的力量\N{\rEng}She was able to explain powers invisible,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.35,1:11:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,电磁场和力…\N{\rEng}electromagnetic fields and forces...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.57,1:11:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,精灵正是由这些构成的\N{\rEng}The very stuff of which djinn are made.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:58.70,1:12:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,你是电磁场？\N{\rEng}You're electromagnetic?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.44,1:12:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,就像你是尘土构成，我是由精妙之火构成的\N{\rEng}As you are dust, I am made of subtle fire.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.36,1:12:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,当她要生孩子的时候\N{\rEng}And when she was to bear a child,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.80,1:12:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,我被幸福所困扰\N{\rEng}I was plagued with happiness,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.10,1:12:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,因为我知道这将使我们的关系更紧密\N{\rEng}for I knew it would strengthen us.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.37,1:12:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,她怀了你的孩子？\N{\rEng}She was carrying your child?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.72,1:12:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,一个由火和尘土组成的孩子\N{\rEng}A child, of fire and dust.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:19.63,1:12:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,那么，是哪里出了问题？\N{\rEng}So, where did it go wrong?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.64,1:12:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Alithea，我爱她\N{\rEng}Alithea, I loved her.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:24.64,1:12:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,我爱她狂热的思想\N{\rEng}I loved the fervor of her mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.38,1:12:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,我爱她的愤怒\N{\rEng}I loved her anger.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.51,1:12:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,我爱我把她的皱眉\N{\rEng}I loved my power
Dialogue: 0,1:12:28.64,1:12:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,变成微笑的能力\N{\rEng}to turn her frowns into smiles.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.43,1:12:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我爱她胜过爱Sheba\N{\rEng}I loved her more than Sheba.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.91,1:12:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,更胜过你的自由？\N{\rEng}More than your own freedom?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:37.48,1:12:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rEng}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.96,1:12:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,留住她，继续做她的俘虏\N{\rEng}It became my greatest desire to... to keep her,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:42.48,1:12:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,成为我最大的愿望…\N{\rEng}to remain her prisoner.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.62,1:12:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,一想到要获得自由，就会让我心生厌恶\N{\rEng}The thought of being set free sickened my heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.37,1:12:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,我发现自己阻止了她，以免她许第三个愿\N{\rEng}I caught myself stopping her lest she make her third wish.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:58.67,1:13:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,哦,天哪\N{\rEng}Oh, gosh.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.77,1:13:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,我把事情搞砸了\N{\rEng}I made a mess of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.03,1:13:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,她开始指责我陷害她\N{\rEng}She began to accuse me of trapping her,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.03,1:13:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,就像她丈夫一样\N{\rEng}-like her husband.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.82,1:13:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我试着去弥补\N{\rEng}I tried to make amends.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.00,1:13:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,为了赎罪，我会把自己放进瓶子里\N{\rEng}To atone, I would put myself in the bottle.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.57,1:13:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,被封住\N{\rEng}To be sealed.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:23.13,1:13:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,那样的话，她就能对我有更大的影响力\N{\rEng}That way, she could have more power over me.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.19,1:13:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,瓶子里什么都没有\N{\rEng}To be nothing in a bottle.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.93,1:13:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,我可以为她这样做\N{\rEng}I could do that for her.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.50,1:13:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,每一次，都会起作用\N{\rEng}And every time, it would appease.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:47.11,1:13:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,每一次，除了最后那次\N{\rEng}Every time, except for the last.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:50.73,1:13:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,那时，像一阵突然的暴风雨\N{\rEng}When, like a sudden squall, all thunder and lightning,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:55.47,1:13:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,她开始嚎啕大哭，说:“\N{\rEng}she began to weep and wail, and said,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:58.47,1:14:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,我希望我能忘记我曾经见过你  ”\N{\rEng}"I wish I could forget I ever met you."
Dialogue: 0,1:14:07.05,1:14:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,她做到了，就在那一刻\N{\rEng}And she did, on the instant.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:14.84,1:14:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,她出来了  我进去了\N{\rEng}She was out. I was in.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:17.75,1:14:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,她已经忘记了我\N{\rEng}She'd forgotten me.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:21.02,1:14:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Alithea, 怎么会这样…\N{\rEng}Alithea, how can it be...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:26.07,1:14:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,完全爱一个人是个错误？\N{\rEng}a mistake to love someone entirely?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.83,1:14:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,我有一个愿望\N{\rEng}I have a wish.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:00.97,1:15:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,然而，我担心这可能是一个过分的要求\N{\rEng}However, I'm afraid it may be too much to ask.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:08.80,1:15:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,在我能力范围内吗？\N{\rEng}Is it within my power?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:11.55,1:15:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,我希望如此  我确实希望如此\N{\rEng}I hope so. I do hope so.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.12,1:15:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,这是你的心愿吗？\N{\rEng}Is it your heart's desire?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.86,1:15:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,是的，我很确定\N{\rEng}Yeah, I'm certain of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:36.66,1:15:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,看，呃\N{\rEng}See, erm,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:38.66,1:15:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我是来爱你的\N{\rEng}I'm here to love you.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.80,1:15:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,而且，呃\N{\rEng}And, uh,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.58,1:15:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,我希望你能爱我作为回报\N{\rEng}I wish for you to love me in return.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.85,1:15:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,你想让我们做爱的工艺品？\N{\rEng}You want us to make love-craft?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.20,1:15:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,是的，那也可以\N{\rEng}Yeah, that too.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:57.29,1:15:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,所有的\N{\rEng}All of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:58.46,1:16:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,你会为此放弃自己吗？\N{\rEng}And you would abandon yourself to this?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:04.34,1:16:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rEng}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:06.03,1:16:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rEng}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:09.30,1:16:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我希望我们的孤独能在一起\N{\rEng}I want our solitudes to be together.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.30,1:16:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,我想要在不朽的故事中描述的那种爱\N{\rEng}I want that love professed in ageless tales.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.05,1:16:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,我想要你对Sheba,女王的那种渴望\N{\rEng}I want that longing you felt for the Queen of Sheba,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:22.57,1:16:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,以及你给你的天才Zefir的那种爱\N{\rEng}and that love you gave to your genius, Zefir.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:26.32,1:16:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,我想要它\N{\rEng}I want it.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:40.94,1:16:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,我？\N{\rEng}Me?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.33,1:16:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,你\N{\rEng}You.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:52.65,1:16:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,你？\N{\rEng}You?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:55.87,1:16:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,我\N{\rEng}Me.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.66,1:17:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,这是不是太过分了？\N{\rEng}Is it too much?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.10,1:17:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,这要求过分吗？\N{\rEng}Is it all too much to ask?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:28.77,1:17:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,来吧\N{\rEng}Come.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.13,1:17:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,我们该如何处理被唤醒的渴望？\N{\rEng}What are we to do with longings awoken?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:46.66,1:17:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,我怎么才能让你相信\N{\rEng}How can I persuade you
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.09,1:17:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,我曾经爱上过一个精灵？\N{\rEng}that I once found love with a djinn?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:52.66,1:17:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,无论如何，很少有人会相信我\N{\rEng}In any case, few would believe me.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:57.15,1:18:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,爱不是我们凭理智得到的东西\N{\rEng}Love is not something we come to by reason.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.06,1:18:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,它更像是一种蒸汽\N{\rEng}It's more like a vapor,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:05.15,1:18:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,也许是一个梦\N{\rEng}a dream, perhaps,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.33,1:18:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,引诱我们进入\N{\rEng}to lure us into the enchantment
Dialogue: 0,1:18:09.29,1:18:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,我们自己的故事中\N{\rEng}of our own stories.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.47,1:18:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,如果是这样的话\N{\rEng}If that's so,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.34,1:18:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,我们怎么知道它是否是真实的？\N{\rEng}how are we to know if it's ever real?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:18.30,1:18:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,这是事实，还是单纯的疯狂？\N{\rEng}Is it a truth, or simply a madness?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:08.91,1:19:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,我今天动身去伦敦\N{\rEng}I leave for London today.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:11.31,1:19:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,你愿意和我一起回家吗？\N{\rEng}Will you come home with me?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.27,1:19:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,现在这地方可不容易\N{\rEng}It's not such an easy place nowadays.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:19.23,1:19:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,但如果你在那里会更好\N{\rEng}But it'll be better if you're there.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:31.41,1:19:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,请过来\N{\rEng}-Over here, please.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:35.16,1:19:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,举高手\N{\rEng}Hands up.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:44.78,1:19:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,请出来\N{\rEng}-Please step out.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.91,1:19:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,你的口袋里有什么？\N{\rEng}What is in your pockets?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:49.00,1:19:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh\N{\rEng}Oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.09,1:19:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,是一个空瓶子和一个盖子\N{\rEng}Uh, it's an empty bottle and a top.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:55.31,1:19:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,请通过X射线\N{\rEng}Please put it through X-ray.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:56.92,1:19:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,它非常精致\N{\rEng}It is very delicate,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:58.05,1:19:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,我不想它被损坏\N{\rEng}and I don't want it to get damaged.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.44,1:20:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,它不会被损坏的，请通过X射线\N{\rEng}It will not be damaged. Please put through X-ray.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.27,1:20:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,我希望它不要被放在…\N{\rEng}I would prefer that it didn't go in the...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:02.44,1:20:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,护照  登机证\N{\rEng}Passport. Boarding pass.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:05.10,1:20:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢你\N{\rEng}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:16.59,1:20:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,它很脆弱\N{\rEng}It's quite fragile.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.85,1:20:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,女士\N{\rEng}Madam.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:23.25,1:20:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,这是个盐罐\N{\rEng}It's a saltshaker.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:32.61,1:20:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh\N{\rEng}Oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:34.39,1:20:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,别，别过x光，求你了！\N{\rEng}No! No X-ray! Please!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:36.57,1:20:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,站住，女士，站住\N{\rEng}Stop, madam, stop.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:55.32,1:20:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,女士\N{\rEng}Madam.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:56.98,1:20:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh\N{\rEng}Oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.93,1:21:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,你自己独处一会吧\N{\rEng}In your own time.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:36.99,1:22:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,这里的空气很浓稠\N{\rEng}The air is thick here.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.17,1:22:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,充满了坚持的声音和匆忙的面孔\N{\rEng}Full of insistent voices and rushing faces.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:44.74,1:22:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,哦？\N{\rEng}Oh?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:46.48,1:22:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,就像小爱因斯坦？\N{\rEng}Like Tiny Einstein?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:49.26,1:22:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,电视和电话塔之类的？\N{\rEng}Television, and phone towers, and such?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:51.44,1:22:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rEng}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.18,1:22:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,是的，你所有精巧的设备\N{\rEng}Yes. All your ingenious devices
Dialogue: 0,1:22:56.97,1:22:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,都在同时喃喃自语\N{\rEng}all murmuring at once.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.75,1:23:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,弯下头\N{\rEng}Bend your head.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:07.33,1:23:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,你都听到了？\N{\rEng}You hear all that?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.24,1:23:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,我也看到并感受到了\N{\rEng}I also see it and feel it.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:15.25,1:23:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,我是一个发射器\N{\rEng}I am a transmitter.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.25,1:23:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,这会不会太多了？\N{\rEng}Isn't it all too much?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:21.17,1:23:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,我是一个精灵\N{\rEng}I am a djinn.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:22.47,1:23:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,我可以适应\N{\rEng}I can adapt.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.56,1:23:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,我很快就会习惯的\N{\rEng}I'll soon get used to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:27.35,1:23:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,她回来了\N{\rEng}She's back.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.22,1:23:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,我相信她回来了\N{\rEng}I believe she's back.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:30.57,1:23:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,她和别人在一起吗？\N{\rEng}Is she with someone?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:32.52,1:23:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,不，我觉得她又在自言自语了\N{\rEng}No, I think she's talking to herself again.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.57,1:23:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,你好,Clementine\N{\rEng}Hello, Clementine.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:36.31,1:23:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Fanny  你还好吗？\N{\rEng}Fanny. Are you well?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:38.66,1:23:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,你遇到什么麻烦了吗？\N{\rEng}Did you have any trouble?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.49,1:23:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,麻烦?什么样的麻烦？\N{\rEng}Trouble? What kind of trouble?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:42.66,1:23:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,和你的外国朋友有关的\N{\rEng}With your foreign friends.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.49,1:23:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,因为我们经常问自己\N{\rEng}Because we often ask ourselves,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:46.41,1:23:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么Binnie 博士要浪费她的时间和智慧\N{\rEng}"Why would Dr. Binnie waste her time and intelligence
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.11,1:23:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,去研究别人的方式而不是坚持我们自己的方式？\N{\rEng}"studying the ways of others instead of upholding our own?"
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.80,1:23:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,为我们的英国文化感到尴尬，不是吗？\N{\rEng}Embarrassed by our British culture, are we?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:54.33,1:23:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,不  不\N{\rEng}No. No.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.81,1:23:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我反而更有可能对任何人感到尴尬\N{\rEng}I am rather more likely to be embarrassed by anybody
Dialogue: 0,1:23:58.20,1:24:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,反射性地对任何不同的人感到害怕\N{\rEng}reflexly frightened of anybody different.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:00.55,1:24:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,你到底在说什么？\N{\rEng}What exactly are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:01.68,1:24:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,她说我们是偏执狂\N{\rEng}She's calling us bigots.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:03.47,1:24:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,你说的，不是我说的\N{\rEng}Your word, not mine.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:04.51,1:24:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,你误解了\N{\rEng}You misunderstand.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:05.64,1:24:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,-哦?  -那不是他们的样子，亲爱的\N{\rEng}-Oh? -It's not how they look, dear.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.17,1:24:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是他们的生活方式  他们相信什么\N{\rEng}It's how they live. What they believe.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.69,1:24:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,-他们吃  -你在说什么？\N{\rEng}-What they eat. -What are you on about?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.43,1:24:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,无论到哪里，都有种族问题\N{\rEng}Everywhere one goes, ethnics.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:12.26,1:24:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,我们被淹没了，我们正在招致我们的厄运\N{\rEng}We are being overwhelmed, and we're inviting our doom.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:15.26,1:24:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,这不是自然的\N{\rEng}It's not natural.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:16.61,1:24:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,鸟属于空中  鱼属于大海\N{\rEng}Birds belong in the air. Fish belong in the sea.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:18.74,1:24:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是上帝希望我们成为的样子\N{\rEng}And that is how the good Lord meant us to be.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.05,1:24:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,你从头到尾只是在胡说八道\N{\rEng}You're just spouting rubbish from start to finish.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.10,1:24:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,这是科学  这是科学事实\N{\rEng}It's science. It's a scientific fact.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:24.62,1:24:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,-这是一个错误的类比\N{\rEng}-It's a false analogy.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:25.88,1:24:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,我是说，动物确实有自然栖息地\N{\rEng}I mean, animals do have a natural habitat.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.15,1:24:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,这是真的，但人类有能力\N{\rEng}It's true, but human beings are capable
Dialogue: 0,1:24:30.36,1:24:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,生活在任何他们选择的环境中\N{\rEng}of living in any environment they bloody well choose.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:32.50,1:24:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,-那不是事实\N{\rEng}-That's not a fact.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:33.72,1:24:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,-你在说什么?  -这是一个观点\N{\rEng}-What are you saying? -It's an opinion.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:35.37,1:24:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,并且你错了\N{\rEng}And you're wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:36.59,1:24:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我再也忍不下去了\N{\rEng}I'm not putting up with any more of this.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:38.07,1:24:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,走吧，Clem  让那个疯女人去吧\N{\rEng}Come away, Clem. Let the crazy lady be.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:40.29,1:24:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我们永远无法从她嘴里得到有价值的东西\N{\rEng}We're never gonna get any sense out of her.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:42.20,1:24:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,我以前从没对你说过这话\N{\rEng}You know, I've never said this to you before.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:45.12,1:24:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,但你们两个都很可怜\N{\rEng}But you're both pitiful.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:47.56,1:24:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,闭上你的小嘴！\N{\rEng}Shut your cakehole!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:48.77,1:24:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,豌豆脑袋和可怜的人\N{\rEng}Pea-brained and pitiful.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:51.86,1:24:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,你，混蛋！\N{\rEng}You, fuckface!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:54.26,1:24:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,让你的常春藤别在我们这边的墙壁上生长！\N{\rEng}Stop your ivy growing on our side of the wall!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:59.35,1:25:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,我为什么要让他们影响我？\N{\rEng}Why do I let them get to me?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:01.53,1:25:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,我应该为他们感到遗憾\N{\rEng}I should feel sorry for them.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:03.62,1:25:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,但这是我的家  这是我的避难所\N{\rEng}But this is my home. It's my sanctuary.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:10.88,1:25:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,-我希望他们…\N{\rEng}-I could wish them...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.15,1:25:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,顺便说一句，这不是一个愿望\N{\rEng}That's not a wish, by the way.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:16.37,1:25:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,-我知道\N{\rEng}-I know.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:21.41,1:27:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,我的精灵\N{\rEng}My djinn.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:23.71,1:27:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,你今天过得怎么样？\N{\rEng}How was your day?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:24.93,1:27:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,每一双倾听的耳朵都是你的\N{\rEng}Every listening ear was yours.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:27.32,1:27:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,还有每一个声音，每一个气味  和每一次触摸\N{\rEng}Every voice, every scent, and touch.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:29.94,1:27:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,你无处不在\N{\rEng}You were everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:36.90,1:27:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,一会儿就回来\N{\rEng}Back in a minute.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.66,1:27:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,这个时候会是谁呢？\N{\rEng}Whoever could that be at this hour?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:59.79,1:28:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,可能是她\N{\rEng}It could be her.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.36,1:28:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Clem  Fanny\N{\rEng}Clem. Fanny.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.32,1:28:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,鹰嘴豆，丁香，开心果\N{\rEng}Chickpeas, cloves, pistachio.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:13.63,1:28:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,他们会在你的嘴里融化\N{\rEng}They melt in your mouth.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:33.35,1:28:34.83,Default,,0,0,0,,这是我的朋友\N{\rEng}This is my friend.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:35.96,1:28:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,他要呆上一段时间\N{\rEng}He'll be staying for a while.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:38.79,1:28:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello\N{\rEng}Hello.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:42.92,1:28:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,-Hello\N{\rEng}-Hello. -Hello.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:48.93,1:28:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,我的精灵告诉我\N{\rEng}My Djinn told me,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:50.71,1:28:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,当他们在精灵界聚在一起时\N{\rEng}when they come together in the Realm of Djinn,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:53.67,1:28:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,他们会互相讲故事\N{\rEng}they tell each other stories.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.63,1:28:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,故事对他们来说就像呼吸一样\N{\rEng}Stories are like breath to them.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:58.76,1:28:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,他们创造了意义\N{\rEng}They make meaning.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:01.81,1:29:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,"是的，"我说\N{\rEng}"Yes," I said.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:03.07,1:29:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,"我们就是这样的"\N{\rEng}"That's just how it is with us."
Dialogue: 0,1:29:05.90,1:29:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,我们讲述的每一个故事\N{\rEng}Each story we tell is a fragment
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.64,1:29:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,都是无尽变形的拼图中的一个片段\N{\rEng}in an endless shape-shifting mosaic.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:11.65,1:29:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,而我们这个小故事，就像所有的故事一样，必须有个结局\N{\rEng}And this small pebble, like all stories, must end.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.74,1:29:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,如果是关于许愿的，那就是一个警示性的故事\N{\rEng}If it's about wishing, it's a cautionary tale.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.00,1:29:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,那么，它怎么会出错呢？\N{\rEng}So, how will it go wrong?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:25.01,1:29:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,也许，它已经出错了\N{\rEng}Perhaps, it already has.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.84,1:29:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,即使真理赤身裸体地站在他们面前\N{\rEng}Even though Truth stood before them naked,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:33.36,1:29:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,他们还是会背过身去\N{\rEng}they turned their backs.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:35.02,1:29:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,于是，“真理”走到一边，在阴影中等待\N{\rEng}So, Truth moved to the side and waited in the shadows.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:39.50,1:29:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,在接下来的日子里\N{\rEng}In the days that followed,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:41.15,1:29:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,精灵会陪伴叙事学家去工作\N{\rEng}the Djinn would accompany the narratologist to her work.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:44.68,1:29:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,当他不和她在一起时\N{\rEng}And when he wasn't with her,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:46.29,1:29:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,他就会去热切地探索这个世界\N{\rEng}he would go in eager exploration of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:52.47,1:29:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,今天我度过了如此奇妙的一天\N{\rEng}Today I had such a marvelous day.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:56.69,1:29:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,我看到了很多东西\N{\rEng}I saw many things.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:59.69,1:30:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,我看着一个人看向另一个人的活生生的大脑\N{\rEng}I watched a human look into the living brain of another
Dialogue: 0,1:30:03.87,1:30:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,并阻止致命的出血\N{\rEng}and arrest a fatal bleeding.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:10.97,1:30:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我参观了对撞机\N{\rEng}I visited the Collider.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:14.06,1:30:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,一个探究物质本质的巨大仪器\N{\rEng}A vast gizmo which probed the essence of matter.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:21.63,1:30:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,然后我看到了一个盘子，一个巨大的盘子\N{\rEng}And then I saw a dish, a great dish
Dialogue: 0,1:30:24.89,1:30:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,它倾听着早已死去的星星的低语\N{\rEng}that listens to the whispers of stars long dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:30.72,1:30:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,人类是…\N{\rEng}Humankind is...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:32.73,1:30:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,是个奇迹，Alithea\N{\rEng}is a wonder, Alithea.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.56,1:30:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,我很高兴你这么想\N{\rEng}I'm happy you think so.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:37.99,1:30:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,自从我被困在Zefir的瓶子里以来\N{\rEng}All of this since I was trapped in Zefir's bottle.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:41.08,1:30:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,所有这一切都在不到200年的时间里发生了惊人的变化\N{\rEng}All these astonishments, in less than 200 years.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:45.87,1:30:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,是的，但，我的意思是\N{\rEng}Yes, but, I mean,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.87,1:30:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,这只是工程和技术\N{\rEng}that's just engineering and technology.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:52.18,1:30:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,尽管有这么多的奇思妙想\N{\rEng}Despite all the whiz-bang,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:54.79,1:30:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我们仍然感到困惑不解\N{\rEng}we remain bewildered.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:59.84,1:31:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,当我们无法控制混乱的时候\N{\rEng}When we can't contain the chaos,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:03.58,1:31:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,我们就会充满恐惧和惊慌\N{\rEng}we are filled with dread and panic,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.19,1:31:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,我们就会互相攻击\N{\rEng}and we turn on each other.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:08.50,1:31:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,当然会这样，你是人\N{\rEng}But of course, you are human.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:11.03,1:31:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,这是你的本性\N{\rEng}That is your nature.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:15.51,1:31:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,是的  所以，故事永远不会改变\N{\rEng}Yeah. So, the story never changes.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:19.86,1:31:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,仇恨占了上风\N{\rEng}Hate prevails.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:22.56,1:31:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,它会转移，比爱更长久\N{\rEng}It metastasizes and outlives love.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.96,1:31:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,我只想谈谈爱\N{\rEng}I just want to talk about love.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:31.61,1:31:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,真是矛盾的一团糟，你们都是\N{\rEng}Such a mess of contradictions, all of you.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:35.66,1:31:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,非常感谢\N{\rEng}Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:36.79,1:31:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,人类,真是一个难题\N{\rEng}Humankind, what a conundrum.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:40.10,1:31:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,你在黑暗中摸索\N{\rEng}You fumble around in the dark,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:42.84,1:31:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,然而，你把你的智慧发挥了很大的作用\N{\rEng}and yet, you herd your intelligence to great effect.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:45.97,1:31:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,这是一个很有意思的故事\N{\rEng}It is quite a story.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:48.89,1:31:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,等不及要看它的发展了\N{\rEng}Cannot wait to see where it goes.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:51.76,1:31:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,或者它会如何结束\N{\rEng}Or how it might end.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:54.03,1:31:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,这也是\N{\rEng}That too.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:55.77,1:31:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,凡人永远不会知道，但精灵可能知道\N{\rEng}A mortal will never know, but a djinn might.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:59.73,1:32:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,一个精灵拥有世界上所有的时间\N{\rEng}A djinn has all the time in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:04.30,1:32:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,你不就是那个幸运儿吗？\N{\rEng}Aren't you the lucky one?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:06.52,1:32:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,也许吧\N{\rEng}Maybe.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:08.87,1:32:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,但你们这些尘埃生物…\N{\rEng}But you creatures of dust have...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:12.13,1:32:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,已经让精灵和天使的\N{\rEng}have managed to eclipse
Dialogue: 0,1:32:13.65,1:32:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,力量和目的黯然失色\N{\rEng}the power and purpose of djinn and angel.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:17.00,1:32:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,你对我们没有用处\N{\rEng}You have no use for us.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:19.22,1:32:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,也许，我们会枯萎\N{\rEng}Perhaps, we will wither and...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:20.62,1:32:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,…然后消逝？  -是的\N{\rEng}-And fade away? -Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:22.14,1:32:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,是的  这曾经是我\N{\rEng}Yeah. Well, that used to be the subject
Dialogue: 0,1:32:24.58,1:32:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,所有讲座和论文的主题\N{\rEng}of all my lectures and papers.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:26.67,1:32:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道\N{\rEng}I know.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:30.58,1:32:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,然而，你却在这里\N{\rEng}And yet, here you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:34.02,1:32:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,无所不能的你\N{\rEng}My impossible.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:38.03,1:32:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rEng}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:51.56,1:32:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,有人吗？\N{\rEng}Hello?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:58.18,1:32:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,我回来了！\N{\rEng}I'm home!
Dialogue: 0,1:33:09.75,1:33:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,有人吗？\N{\rEng}Hello?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:37.08,1:33:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,精灵？\N{\rEng}Djinn?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:42.70,1:33:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我的爱人？\N{\rEng}My love?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:47.92,1:33:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,精灵？\N{\rEng}Djinn.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:53.19,1:33:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,这是什么\N{\rEng}What's this?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:56.97,1:33:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,你能听到我吗？\N{\rEng}Can you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:58.98,1:34:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,精灵，和我说话\N{\rEng}Djinn, speak to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:01.15,1:34:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,试着和我说话\N{\rEng}Try to speak to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:04.68,1:34:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,我许愿你可以和我说话\N{\rEng}I wish you to speak to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:10.86,1:34:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,哦\N{\rEng}Oh...
Dialogue: 0,1:34:26.87,1:34:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我刚刚正在睡觉\N{\rEng}I was sleeping.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:28.92,1:34:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,睡觉\N{\rEng}Sleeping.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:32.88,1:34:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,精灵，别睡\N{\rEng}Djinn don't sleep.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:35.01,1:34:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,我们出去走走\N{\rEng}Let's go for a walk.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:36.32,1:34:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,来次振作精神的远足\N{\rEng}A long, bracing walk.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:37.80,1:34:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,我为我们准备了一些东西\N{\rEng}I have prepared something for us.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:39.36,1:34:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,我都计划好了\N{\rEng}I have it all planned.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:40.97,1:34:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,对我们来说，这是一个美妙的夜晚\N{\rEng}A wonderous night for us.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.15,1:34:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,这一定会很棒的\N{\rEng}It will be amazing.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:45.33,1:34:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,-我们生命中最美好的时光  -停！\N{\rEng}-The best time of our lives. -Stop!
Dialogue: 0,1:34:48.16,1:34:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,这些电磁场，我可以把它们从我头上移开\N{\rEng}These electromagnetic fields, I can push them from my head.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:52.29,1:34:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,我可以把它们移开\N{\rEng}I can push them away.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:54.95,1:34:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我们去野餐\N{\rEng}We'll go for a picnic.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:01.08,1:35:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,我们来弹尤克里里吧\N{\rEng}Ah, we'll play the ukulele.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:05.83,1:35:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Alithea, 这里有我的位置\N{\rEng}Alithea, there is a place for me here.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:09.13,1:35:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,这些力量\N{\rEng}These forces,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:10.40,1:35:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,它们永远不会消失，不会从这个世界上消失\N{\rEng}they will never go away, not from this world.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:12.09,1:35:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,我会战胜他们  我可以帮你\N{\rEng}I will overcome them. I can do that for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:14.31,1:35:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,你是我的Alithea，我爱你\N{\rEng}You are my Alithea, and I love you.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:16.49,1:35:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢你！谢谢你！谢谢你的努力\N{\rEng}Thank you. Thank you. Thank you for trying.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:18.27,1:35:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,你以为我不爱你吗？\N{\rEng}You don't think that I love you?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:20.49,1:35:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,爱是一份礼物\N{\rEng}Love is a gift.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:22.71,1:35:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,这是自己自由给予的礼物\N{\rEng}It's a gift of oneself given freely.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:25.11,1:35:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,这不是乞求就能得到的\N{\rEng}It's not something one can ever ask for.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:28.85,1:35:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我把我俩都骗了\N{\rEng}I tricked us both.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:30.07,1:35:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我说出那个愿望的那一刻\N{\rEng}The moment I spoke that wish,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:31.76,1:35:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,我就剥夺了你实现它的能力\N{\rEng}I took away your power to grant it.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:34.85,1:35:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我比任何人都应该知道这一点\N{\rEng}I, more than anybody, I should've known that.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:39.12,1:35:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我不会再搞砸了\N{\rEng}I'm not going to screw this up again.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:41.30,1:35:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,我的精灵，如果这个世界不适合你\N{\rEng}My Djinn, if this world is not for you,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:45.47,1:35:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,我许愿你能回到属于你的地方\N{\rEng}I wish that you return to where you belong.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:49.17,1:35:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,无论哪里都行\N{\rEng}Wherever that may be.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:29.00,1:37:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs18\b0\bord0\shad0\fad(3200,1500)\pos(192,178)}三年后
Dialogue: 0,1:38:18.54,1:38:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,妈妈！\N{\rEng}Mommy!
Dialogue: 0,1:38:21.63,1:38:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,过来，小猴子\N{\rEng}Come here, little monkey.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:23.68,1:38:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,这不是妈妈\N{\rEng}That's not Mommy.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:53.24,1:39:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿！嘿！嘿！  啊，不！\N{\rEng}Hey, hey, hey! Ah, no!
Dialogue: 0,1:39:54.51,1:39:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,看  联赛中最好的前锋\N{\rEng}Watch it. Top striker in the league.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:05.47,1:40:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,你看到了吗？\N{\rEng}Did you see that?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:10.13,1:40:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,他会时不时来看我\N{\rEng}He would visit from time to time,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:12.74,1:40:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,他们会抓住每一个生动的时刻\N{\rEng}and they would grasp each vivid moment.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:16.22,1:40:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,尽管天空的喧嚣让他很痛苦\N{\rEng}Despite the pain of the raucous skies,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:19.14,1:40:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,但他总是呆很长时间\N{\rEng}he always stayed longer than he should,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:21.79,1:40:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,一直要到她求他离开为止\N{\rEng}long after she begged him to leave.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:25.28,1:40:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,他承诺在她有生之年回来\N{\rEng}He promised to return in her lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:28.50,1:40:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,对她来说，这已经足够了\N{\rEng}and for her, that was more than enough.


